#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Tummy Time Safari*"
msgstr "*Magietyd-Safari*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Time for an adventure - right on the floor! 🌱"
msgstr "Tyd vir 'n avontuur - hier op die vloer🌱"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "✅ Lay a soft blanket on the floor and gently place your baby on their tummy. Put a few colourful toys or soft books just out of reach, and see your baby reach for them. "
msgstr "✅ Plaas 'n sagte kombers op die vloer en sit jou baba versigtig op sy/haar magie neer. Sit 'n paar kleurvolle speelgoed of sagte boekies net buite bereik en kyk hoe baba uitreik daarvoor. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Talk, sing, or lie down face-to-face to keep them engaged."
msgstr "👀 Praat, sing of lê aangesig tot aangesig om hom/haar besig te hou."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🧸 Make it playful - wiggle a toy or a plastic bottle with some rice like an animal exploring the jungle! “Look, here comes a lion!”"
msgstr "🧸 Maak dit speel-speel - wikkel 'n speelding rond, of 'n plastiekbottel met rys in, soos 'n dier wat die oerwoud verken! \"Kyk, hier kom die leeu!\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Tummy time is essential for your baby’s physical development and builds the strength they’ll need to crawl and sit ⭐"
msgstr "Magietyd is noodsaaklik vir jou baba se fisiese ontwikkeling, en dit bou sy/haar krag op wat hy/sy nodig het om te kruip en te sit⭐"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Face to Face Fun*"
msgstr "*Aangesig-tot-Aangesig-Pret*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Babies love looking at faces - especially yours! 😃"
msgstr "Babas hou daarvan om na gesigte te kyk - veral joune! 😃"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👑 Sit comfortably and hold your baby so you’re face-to-face. Make funny faces, raise your eyebrows, puff your cheeks, and talk or sing gently."
msgstr "👑 Sit gemaklik en hou jou baba so dat julle na mekaar kyk. Trek snaakse gesigte, lig jou wenkbroue, blaas jou wange op en gesels of sing saggies."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🚩 Watch as your baby starts to copy you! Peek-a-boo and big smiles are great ways to bond."
msgstr "🚩 Kyk hoe jou baba jou naboots! Koekeloerspeletjies en breë glimlaggies is wonderlike maniere om 'n band te vorm."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This activity helps your baby develop emotional connection, eye contact, and early social skills - all while having fun together 🎉"
msgstr "Hierdie aktiwiteit help jou baba om emosionele verbondenheid, oogkontak en vroeë sosiale vaardighede te ontwikkel - alles terwyl julle pret het 🎉"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Sing & Sway*"
msgstr "*Sing & Swaai*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎵 Hold your baby close and gently sway together to the rhythm of a soft song. You can hum or sing a lullaby as you move, making eye contact and smiling as you go."
msgstr "🎵 Hou jou baba vas en swaai sagkens op die ritme van 'n sagte liedjie. Jy kan neurie of 'n wiegeliedjie sing terwyl jy beweeg; maak oogkontak en glimlag terwyl jy beweeg."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Try singing the same song each day - it creates a lovely routine and helps your baby recognise familiar sounds over time."
msgstr "🔄 Probeer om elke dag dieselfde liedjie te sing - dit skep 'n goeie roetine en dit help jou baba om, met verloop van tyd, bekende klanke te herken."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "The soothing movement helps your baby feel safe and connected, while the sound of your voice supports early language development and emotional bonding 💛"
msgstr "Die strelende bewegings help dat jou baba veilig en verbonde voel, terwyl jou stem vroeë taalontwikkeling en emosionele verbondenheid ondersteun 💛"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "It’s a simple, calming way to bond and build your baby’s growing brain through rhythm, movement, and love 🌙"
msgstr "Dis 'n eenvoudige, kalmerende manier om 'n band te vorm en jou baba se groeiende brein deur ritme, beweging en liefde te bou 🌙"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Toe Tickle Talk*"
msgstr "*Toonkielie-Geselsies*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let’s explore toes and fingers with a gentle tickle and some fun words! 👋"
msgstr "Kom ons verken die tone en vingers met 'n sagte gekielie en 'n paar prettige woorde👋"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "▶️ Start by wiggling your baby’s toes or fingers one at a time while counting them, saying your own silly rhyme, or simply naming the toes and fingers: “Tickle your tiny toe!” or “Hello little thumb!”"
msgstr "▶️ Begin deur jou baba se tone of vingers een vir een te wikkel terwyl jy dit tel en jou eie verspotte rympies sê, of om eenvoudig net die tone en vingers te noem: \"Kielie jou kleintoontjie!\" of \"Hallo, klein duimpie!\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This activity strengthens your baby’s awareness of their body and supports early language learning - all while sharing giggles and smiles 🎉"
msgstr "Hierdie aktiwiteit versterk jou baba se bewustheid van sy/haar liggaam en dit ondersteun vroeë taalvaardighede - alles terwyl julle saam giggel en glimlag🎉"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Follow the Sound*"
msgstr "*Volg die Klank*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let’s explore the world of sound! 📻"
msgstr "Kom ons verken die wêreld van klanke! 📻"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 Find something in your house that makes a gentle sound, like some rice in a packet or a plastic bag. "
msgstr "💡 Kry iets in die huis wat 'n sagte geluid maak, soos rys in 'n pakkie of 'n plastieksak. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂 Gently make a sound with the object near your baby’s ear - first on one side, then pause and try the other."
msgstr "👂 Maak saggies 'n geluid met die voorwerp naby jou baba se oor - eers aan die een kant, wag, probeer dan die ander kant."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Watch how your baby turns their head to follow the noise. You can even say, “Over here!” as you move the sound."
msgstr "👀 Kyk hoe jou baba sy/haar kop draai om die geluid te volg. Jy kan ook sê: \"Hierdie kant\" wanneer jy die klank beweeg."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This is a lovely, quiet way to play together - and it helps your baby start to understand how sound connects to movement. It supports their attention and brain development 🌱"
msgstr "Dit is 'n wonderlike, vinnige manier om saam te speel - en dit help jou baba om te verstaan hoe klank met beweging verband hou. Dit ondersteun sy/haar aandagspan- en breinontwikkeling 🌱"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Story Cuddles*"
msgstr "* Storiedrukkies*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "It’s never too early to share a story! 📖"
msgstr "Dis nooit te vroeg om 'n storie te deel nie! 📖"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂 Hold your baby close and tell them a simple story – you can tell them about your day or memories from when you were young, or you can make up a short story."
msgstr "👂 Hou jou baba vas en vertel 'n eenvoudige storie - jy kan hom/haar vertel van jou dag of herinneringe van jou jonger self, of jy kan 'n kort storie opmaak."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💙 Your baby may not understand what you are saying yet, but the sound of your voice, your expressions, and the closeness all help them feel safe and connected."
msgstr "💙 Jou baba verstaan dalk nog nie wat jy sê nie, maar die geluid van jou stem, jou gesigsuitdrukkings en nabyheid help dat hy/sy veilig en verbonde voel."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 If you share a story from a book, you can point to pictures and describe what you see: “Look, a dog! The dog is playing outside.”"
msgstr "👀 As jy 'n storie uit 'n boek deel, kan jy na die prentjies wys en beskryf wat jy sien: \"Kyk, 'n hond! Die hond speel buite.\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Story telling builds language, imagination, and a love of stories and reading - right from the start. And cuddling up together makes it even more special ✨"
msgstr "Om 'n storie te vertel, bou taalvaardigheid, verbeelding en 'n liefde vir stories en lees - reg van die begin af. En om snoesig saam te wees, maak dit baie meer spesiaal ✨"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Name That Sound*"
msgstr "*Benoem Daardie Klank*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Make everyday noises into a fun game! 🎵"
msgstr "Omskep alledaagse geluide in 'n prettige speletjie!🎵"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔑 Use objects like a crinkly bag, keys, or tapping a cup. Make a sound and then pause."
msgstr "🔑 Gebruik voorwerpe soos 'n kreukelrige sak, sleutels, of tik op 'n koppie. Maak 'n geluid en wag dan."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂 Say what it is: “Crinkle, crinkle! That’s the bag!” or “Clink clink! That’s the keys!” Watch your baby’s reaction - do they turn toward the sound? Do they smile or blink?"
msgstr "👂 Sê wat dit is: \"Kreukel-kreukel! Dis die sak!\" of \"Rinkel-rinkel! Dis die sleutels!\" Hou dop hoe jou baba reageer - draai hy/sy na die geluid? Glimlag hy/sy of knip hy/sy sy/haar oë?"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This activity builds your baby’s listening and attention skills while helping them begin to link sounds to the world around them."
msgstr "Hierdie aktiwiteit bou jou baba se luister- en aandagvaardighede; dit help ook om 'n band met die wêreld om ons te vorm."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Even the smallest sounds can open up a big world of discovery! 🌈"
msgstr "Selfs die kleinste geluide kan 'n groot wêreld van ontdekking oopmaak! 🌈"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Follow the Beat*"
msgstr "*Hou die Ritme*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎵 Use your hands to gently clap or pat a simple rhythm on your little one’s legs or arms: “Ta-ta-ta... ta-ta!”"
msgstr "🎵 Gebruik jou hande om saggies te klap, of tik 'n eenvoudige ritme op jou kleinding se been of arm uit: \"Ta-ta-ta ... ta-ta!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "😃 Then pause and smile - do they respond? Your little one may wiggle, kick, or if they are a bit older they may even copy the rhythm."
msgstr "😃 Wag dan en glimlag - reageer hy/sy? Jou kleinding sal dalk wikkel, skop, of as hy/sy 'n bietjie ouer is, sal hy/sy dalk die ritme naboots."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This playful call-and-response builds listening, rhythm, and connection - just like traditional music has done for generations 💚"
msgstr "Hierdie prettige roep-en-reageer bou luister, ritme en verbondenheid - net soos tradisionele musiek vir generasies gedoen het💚"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Scarf Peekabo*"
msgstr "*Serp-Koekeloer*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "It’s peekaboo time - with a twist! 🎁"
msgstr "Dis koekeloertyd - met 'n kinkel! 🎁"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔶 Grab a soft scarf or cloth and gently hide your face behind it. "
msgstr "🔶 Gryp 'n sagte serp of lap en steek jou gesig daaragter weg. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 Then slowly pull it away and say, “Peekaboo!” with a big smile."
msgstr "👋 Haal dit stadig van jou gesig weg en sê, \"Daar's hy!\" met 'n groot glimlag."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🧸 Try hiding your baby’s favourite toy or your baby’s feet too. Each reveal is a surprise, sparking joy and curiosity!"
msgstr "🧸 Probeer om ook jou baba se gunstelingspeelding of jou baba se voete weg te steek. Elke onthulling is 'n verrassing, wat vreugde en nuuskierigheid teweegbring!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This playful activity encourages visual tracking, helps build anticipation, and supports early social interaction 👀"
msgstr "Hierdie prettige aktiwiteit moedig visuele navolging aan, dit help om afwagting te skep, en ondersteun vroeë sosiale interaksie 👀"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Peekaboo is more than just fun - it teaches your baby that things (and people!) still exist, even when they’re out of sight ✨"
msgstr "Koekeloer is meer as net pret - dit leer jou baba dat dinge (en mense) steeds bestaan, al is hulle ook buite sig ✨"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from UNICEF Playbox: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=trQ1tFuagzQ"
msgstr "Aangepas uit die UNICEF Playbox: https//www.youtube.com/watch?v=trQ1tFuagzQ"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Mirror Moments*"
msgstr "*Spieël-Oomblikke*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "It’s time to meet someone special - themselves! 👋"
msgstr "Dis tyd om iemand spesiaals te ontmoet - hom-/haarself! 👋"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "😃 Stand in front of a mirror or reflecting window with your little one and watch their reaction. "
msgstr "😃 Staan voor die spieël of 'n weerkaatsende venster met jou klein ding en hou hul reaksie dop. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 You can point to their nose or eyes and name them aloud: “There’s your nose!”"
msgstr "👀 Jy kan na hul neus of oë wys en dit hardop noem: \"Daar's jou neus!\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Texture Treasure Hunt*"
msgstr "*Tekstuur-Skattejag*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let’s explore the world through touch! 🌱"
msgstr "Kom ons verken die wêreld deur aanraking! 🌱"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "✅ Collect safe objects with different textures - like a soft sock, a wooden spoon, a smooth ball, or a crinkly wrapper. "
msgstr "✅ Versamel veilige voorwerpe met verskillende teksture - soos 'n sagte sokkie, 'n houtlepel. 'n gladde bal, of gekreukelde papier."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 Gently guide your baby’s hands over each item and describe them: “Soft,” “Bumpy,” “Cold.”"
msgstr "👋 Lei jou baba se hand saggies oor die item en beskryf dit: \"sag,\" \"hobbelrig,\" \"koud\"."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🧸 Encourage older babies to choose what they want to touch. You can even let them sit in or next to a basket with the objects and explore freely."
msgstr "🧸 Moedig ouer babas aan om self te kies wat hulle wil aanraak. Jy kan hulle selfs in of langs die mandjie met die voorwerpe laat sit en vryelik verken."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This sensory activity helps develop touch, language, and curiosity - and it’s perfect for quiet bonding time ⭐"
msgstr "Hierdie sensoriese aktiwiteit help om aanraking, taal en nuuskierigheid in jou kind te ontwikkel - en dis perfek om 'n nouer band met jou kind te vorm ⭐"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Playtime with Books*"
msgstr "*Speeltyd met Boeke*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Reading to your baby from birth is a beautiful way to bond and support their development - even before they understand the words 📖"
msgstr "Om voor geboorte al vir jou baba te lees, is 'n pragtige manier om 'n band te vorm en sy/haar ontwikkeling te ondersteun - selfs voordat hy/sy die woorde verstaan 📖"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⏰ Choose a quiet moment, turn off distractions like TV and phones, and pick a baby-friendly book or even an old magazine or newspaper you have lying around!"
msgstr "⏰ Kies 'n stil oomblik, skakel enige afleidings af, soos televisie en fone, kies 'n baba-vriendelike boek of selfs 'n ou tydskrif of koerant wat daar rondlê!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💚 Talk about the pictures, make sounds, and repeat simple words. Your baby will love hearing your voice - even if they don’t understand yet."
msgstr "💚 Praat oor die prentjies, maak geluide en herhaal eenvoudige woorde. Jou baba sal baie daarvan hou om jou stem te hoor - selfs al verstaan hy/sy nog nie."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Follow their lead - if they lose interest, that’s okay. Keep it short and fun! 😃"
msgstr "Volg sy/haar leiding - as hy/sy belangstelling verloor, is dit oukei. Hou dit kort en prettig! 😃"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 If possible, start a regular routine to read together when your child isn’t too tired or hungry.\rReading together for a few minutes a day is one of the best ways to help your child learn words and connect with you!"
msgstr "🔄 Indien moontlik, begin jou gereelde roetine om saam te lees wanneer jou kind nie honger of moeg is nie.\rOm vir 'n paar minute op 'n dag saam te lees, is een van die beste maniere om jou kind te help om nuwe woorde te leer en 'n band met jou te vorm!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Act Out Emotions*"
msgstr "*Druk Emosies Uit*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let’s have some fun expressing feelings! 😃"
msgstr "Kom laat ons pret hê deur ons emosies uit te druk! 😃"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Tell your child, “Let’s see what it looks like when I am happy!”. Act out a happy face and name the emotion again. "
msgstr "👀 Sê vir jou kind: \"Kom ons kyk hoe dit lyk wanneer ons gelukkig is!\" Maak 'n gelukkige gesig en noem weer die emosie. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "😔 Then try other emotions, like angry, sad, or surprised. Using a gentle voice, you can explain different reasons why you are feeling that emotion."
msgstr "😔 Probeer dan ander emosies soos kwaad, hartseer of verras. Jy kan in 'n sagte stemtoon verskillende redes verduidelik waarom jy daardie emosie voel."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This isn’t just a game - it’s a chance for your child to learn how to recognize emotions in others 💚 "
msgstr "Dit is nie net 'n speletjie nie - dis 'n geleentheid vir jou kind om te leer om emosies in ander te herken 💚 "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "By understanding facial expressions, they’ll strengthen their connections with others and develop empathy 💛"
msgstr "Deur gesigsuitdrukkings te verstaan, sal hy/sy sy/haar verbintenisse met ander versterk en empatie ontwikkel 💛"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "So, get ready to act out some emotions and enjoy this special play activity together! 🌈"
msgstr "So, maak gereed om 'n paar emosies uit te druk en hierdie spesiale speelaktiwiteit saam te geniet! 🌈"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from I am Safe, Loved, and Learning by Save the Children"
msgstr "Aangepas uit I am Safe, Loved, and Learning deur Save the Children"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Animal Sounds & Moves*"
msgstr "*Dieregeluide & -bewegings*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let’s roar like a lion or flap like a bird! ⭐"
msgstr "Kom ons brul soos 'n leeu of flap soos 'n voel! ⭐"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📖 Show your baby a soft animal toy or picture and say its name: “This is a lion - roooar!” "
msgstr "📖 Wys vir jou baba 'n sagte dierespeelding of prentjie en sê sy naam: \"Dit is 'n leeu - bruuuul!\" "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🌱 For younger babies, act it out during tummy time. Older babies might copy your sounds or movements."
msgstr "🌱 Doen dit vir jonger babas tydens magietyd. Ouer babas sal jou dalk naboots en die geluide of bewegings namaak."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂 Talk to your baby as you play: “The cow says moo!” Pause and wait for their reaction, even a smile or babble."
msgstr "👂 Praat met jou baba terwyl julle speel: \"Die koei sê moe!\" Wag vir sy/haar reaksie, selfs 'n glimlag of gebabbel."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This gentle game builds language, movement, and bonding – one animal at a time! 💛"
msgstr "Hierdie kalm speletjie bou taal, beweging en verbondenheid – een dier op 'n slag! 💛"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/act-like-an-animal"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/act-like-an-animal"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Rolling Ball Fun*"
msgstr "*Pret met 'n Rollende Bal*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Time for a rolling game! 🔵"
msgstr "Tyd vir 'n rolspeletjie! 🔵"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 Sit facing your child and gently roll a soft ball (or something else round) back and forth between you. Say their name as you pass it: “Here it comes, Sisi!”"
msgstr "👋 Sit teenoor jou kind en rol 'n sagte bal (of iets anders wat rond is) saggies heen en weer tussen julle. Sê sy/haar naam terwyl jy dit rol: \"Hier kom dit, Sussie!\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💛 Cheer them on as they roll it back to you. You can even add a song or count the rolls out loud."
msgstr "💛 Moedig hom/haar aan terwyl hy/sy dit terugrol. Jy kan selfs 'n liedjie byvoeg of die aantal rolle aftel."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This fun and easy game helps your toddler practise turn-taking, hand-eye coordination, and early social skills - all while enjoying playful connection 🎈"
msgstr "Hierdie prettige en maklike speletjie leer jou kleuter om sy/haar beurt af te wag, hand-oog-koördinasie, en vroeë sosiale vaardighede - alles terwyl julle dit speel-speel geniet en 'n band vorm🎈"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Cup Stack Challenge*"
msgstr "*Koppiestapel-Uitdaging*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🍚 Grab some plastic cups or small containers and show your child how to stack them one by one. "
msgstr "🍚 Gryp 'n paar plastiekkoppies of -houertjies en wys jou kind hoe om dit een vir een opmekaar te stapel. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⬆️ How high can you build your tower?"
msgstr "⬆️ Hoe hoog kan jy jou toring bou?"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎉 Knocking it down is just as fun - watch it fall, then build again!"
msgstr "🎉 Om dit om te gooi, is net soveel pret - kyk hoe dit val, en bou dit dan weer!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This playful activity supports fine motor skills, concentration, and problem-solving - and your child will love seeing what happens each time they try 💡"
msgstr "Hierdie prettige speletjie ondersteun fyn motoriese vaardighede, konsentrasie en probleemoplossing - jou kind sal dit geniet om te sien wat elke keer gebeur wanneer julle probeer 💡"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Dance Mirror*"
msgstr "* Spieëldans*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let’s get moving and dancing together! ⭐"
msgstr "Kom ons beweeg en dans saam! ⭐"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 Turn on some music or sing a song, and start copying your child’s moves - if they clap, you clap! If they wiggle, you wiggle!"
msgstr "👋 Sit bietjie musiek aan of sing 'n liedjie en begin om jou kind se bewegings na te boots - as hy/sy klap, klap jy ook! As hy/sy wikkel, wikkel jy ook!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Then switch and see if they’ll follow your moves."
msgstr "👀 Ruil dan om en kyk of hy/sy jou bewegings naboots."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This back-and-forth dance helps build confidence, strengthens your bond, and supports early communication skills."
msgstr "Hierdie heen-en-weer-dansery help om selfvertroue te bou, dit maak die band tussen julle sterker en ondersteun vroeë kommunikasievaardighede."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "It’s a joyful, silly way to connect through rhythm, music, and play 💚"
msgstr "Dis 'n vreugdevolle, lawwe manier om 'n band te vorm deur ritme, musiek en spel 💚"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Guess the Animal*"
msgstr "* Raai Watter Dier*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let’s guess the animal! 🧸"
msgstr "Kom ons raai watter dier dit is! 🧸"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂 Make a sound like a cow (“moo!”) or a dog (“woof!”) and ask your child, “Which animal is that?”"
msgstr "👂 Maak 'n geluid soos 'n koei (\"moe\") of 'n hond (\"woef\") en vra vir jou kind. \"Watter dier is dit?\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⭐ You can point out animals you see, use toys, or just act it out yourself! "
msgstr "⭐ Jy kan diere wat jy sien, uitwys, of speelgoed gebruik, of jy kan die diere self naboots! "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Then switch and ask them to make the noise - you’ll be surprised how many they know."
msgstr "👀 Ruil dan om en vra hom/haar om die geluid te maak - jy sal verbaas wees hoeveel hy/sy ken."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This fun game builds memory, language skills, and listening - all through the power of play and imagination ✅"
msgstr "Hierdie prettige speletjie bou geheue, taal- en luistervaardighede - alles deur die mag van spel en verbeelding ✅"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Tap & Shake Band*"
msgstr "*Tik-en-Skud-Orkes*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Get ready to make some noise! 🔔"
msgstr "Maak gereed om geraas te maak! 🔔"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🍚 Gather safe household items - pots, plastic containers, spoons, or sealed bottles with rice or beans. "
msgstr "🍚 Maak veilige huishoudelike items bymekaar - potte, plastiekhouers, lepels, of verseëlde bottels met rys of bone daarin. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋Show your toddler how to tap, shake, and bang them together to create sounds."
msgstr "👋 Wys jou kleuter hoe om te tik, skud en dit teen mekaar te slaan om 'n geluid te maak."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎵 Now, make some music and form your own little band! You can sing along or try repeating rhythms together."
msgstr "🎵 Maak nou musiek en begin julle eie orkessie! Julle kan saam sing of probeer om ritmes saam te herhaal."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This activity builds motor skills, rhythm, and listening skills, and gives your toddler a chance to express themselves through sound and movement! ✨"
msgstr "Hierdie aktiwiteit bou motoriese vaardighede, ritme en luistervaardighede. Dit gee jou kleuter 'n geleentheid om hom-/haarself deur klank en beweging uit te druk! ✨"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from UNICEF Playbox: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ha943LSPtTY"
msgstr "Aangepas uit UNICEF Playbox: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ha943LSPtTY"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Where Did It Go*"
msgstr "*Waar Is Dit Heen?*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Time for a little mystery! 🎁"
msgstr "Tyd vir 'n bietjie misterie! 🎁"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🧸 Hide a small toy under a soft cloth or behind your back and ask, “Where did it go?”"
msgstr "🧸 Steek 'n speeldingetjie onder 'n sagte lappie of agter jou rug weg en vra, \"Waar is dit?\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Watch your child pull the cloth away or crawl over to investigate. "
msgstr "👀 Sien hoe jou kind die lappie aftrek of naderkruip om te ondersoek. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Take turns hiding and finding different objects together!"
msgstr "🔄 Maak beurte om voorwerpe saam weg te steek en te vind!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This game helps your toddler develop memory, curiosity, and helps them understand that things still exist even when they’re out of sight! 💡"
msgstr "Hierdie speletjie help jou kleuter met die ontwikkeling van geheue en nuuskierigheid, en help hom/haar om te verstaan dat goed steeds bestaan, al is dit ook buite sig! 💡"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Lap Rhyme Bounce*"
msgstr "*Skootrympie-Hop*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🧸 Sit your baby gently on your lap and bounce them up and down while chanting a simple rhyme you remember from childhood."
msgstr "🧸 Plaas jou baba saggies op jou skoot en laat hom/haar op en af hop terwyl jy 'n eenvoudige rympie uit jou kinderjare sing."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "😃You can speed up or slow down the bounce for extra fun. Add facial expressions or tickles for extra giggles!"
msgstr "😃 Jy kan vinniger of stadiger hop vir ekstra pret. Voeg gesigsuitdrukkings of kielie by vir ekstra giggels!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This rhythmic lap game builds bonding, listening, and body awareness - just like caregivers have done with little ones for generations 💙"
msgstr "Hierdie ritmiese skootspeletjie bou verbondenheid, luistervaardighede en maak hom/haar bewus van sy/haar liggaampie - net soos versorgers vir generasies met kinders gedoen het 💙"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Shadow Play*"
msgstr "*Skaduspel*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Step into a world of imagination and light with this exciting activity! 🌙"
msgstr "Stap 'n wêreld van verbeelding en lig binne met hierdie opwindende aktiwiteit🌙"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 In a darkened room, grab a light and shine it at your hand, casting fun shadows onto the wall. "
msgstr "💡 In 'n donker kamer, vat 'n lig en laat dit op jou hand skyn en maak prettige skaduwees teen die muur. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 Wave at your child and create silly shapes with your fingers - maybe a bunny, a bird, or whatever your imagination dreams up! "
msgstr "👋 Waai vir jou kind en maak snaakse vorms met jou vingers - 'n hasie miskien, 'n voël, of wat ook al jou verbeelding kan opdroom! "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Watch as their curiosity grows, and invite them to try waving their shadow hand back."
msgstr "👀 Hou dop hoe sy/haar nuuskierigheid groei en vra hom/haar om terug te waai vir hul skaduhand."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔑 Encourage your little one to take a turn with the flashlight, giving them the thrill of seeing how light can create different shapes and movements on the wall. "
msgstr "🔑 Moedig jou kleinding aan om hierdie keer met die flits te speel, om die opwinding te ervaar en te sien hoe lig verskillende vorms en bewegings op die muur kan maak. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🏁 Older children might want to join in the fun and make a shadow animal of their own!"
msgstr "🏁 Ouer kinders wil dalk ook deel in die pret om 'n skadudier van hul eie te maak!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This practical experience helps them understand cause and effect, and boosts their creativity and focus as they make shadows ✅"
msgstr "Hierdie praktiese ervaring help hulle om oorsaak-en-gevolg te verstaan, en dit gee hul kreatiwiteit en fokus 'n hupstoot terwyl hulle skaduwees maak ✅"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Zero To Three: https://www.zerotothree.org/resource/play-activities-for-12-to-24-months/"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Zero To Three: https://www.zerotothree.org/resource/play-activities-for-12-to-24-months/"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Mini Obstacle Race*"
msgstr "*Mini-Hinderniswedloop*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Get ready to set up an exciting adventure right in your home! 🚩"
msgstr "Maak gereed vir 'n opwindende avontuur net daar in jou huis!🚩"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔶 Using pillows, chairs, and blankets, create a fun and safe obstacle race for your toddler to explore. "
msgstr "🔶 Gebruik kussings, stoele en komberse om 'n prettige en veilige hinderniswedloop te maak wat jou kleuter kan verken. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 The goal? For your little one to navigate the course by crawling, jumping, and climbing over, under, and through the obstacles."
msgstr "👋 Die doel? Vir jou kleinding om die hindernisbaan te voltooi deur te kruip, spring, oor en onderdeur te klim en deur die hindernisse te gaan."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 As they tackle each challenge, they’ll be developing important gross motor skills like coordination, balance, and strength. "
msgstr "💡 Soos hy/sy elke uitdaging aanpak, sal hy/sy belangrike groot motoriese vaardighede ontwikkel soos koördinasie, balans en krag. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💛Not only will this activity get them moving, but it will also boost their confidence as they conquer each part of the race."
msgstr "💛 Nie net sal hierdie aktiwiteit hom/haar laat beweeg nie, maar dit sal ook sy/haar selfvertroue 'n hupstoot gee, soos hy/sy elke deel van die reis voltooi."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "It’s an easy, playful way to promote physical development while having a great time together! Let the obstacle adventure begin! 🎉"
msgstr "Dis 'n maklike, prettige manier om fisiese ontwikkeling aan te moedig, terwyl julle 'n lekker tyd saam geniet! Laat die hindernis-avontuur begin! 🎉"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Zero To Three: https://www.zerotothree.org/resource/10-olympian-inspired-activity-ideas-for-toddlers/"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Zero To Three: https://www.zerotothree.org/resource/10-olympian-inspired-activity-ideas-for-toddlers/"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Categorising and Organising*"
msgstr "*Kategoriseer en Organiseer*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Help your child to learn by sorting objects and things! 🔵🔷"
msgstr "Help jou kind om te leer deur voorwerpe te sorteer! 🔵🔷"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "By grouping items like a bear as an animal or a mango as a fruit, they’ll start to understand how different things fit together. 🧸"
msgstr "Deur items te groepeer, byvoorbeeld 'n beer as 'n dier, of 'n mango as 'n vrug, sal kinders begin verstaan hoe verskillende goed by mekaar pas. 🧸"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "At home, find safe objects and let them sort them by colour, size, or type - plastic cups and plates are perfect for this! "
msgstr "Vind veilige voorwerpe in die huis en laat hulle dit volgens kleur, grootte of tipes sorteer - plastiekkoppies en -pierings is perfek hiervoor! "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀"
msgstr "👀"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Want to make it more interesting? Try sorting pots and pans by size: Can they fit the small pans into the larger ones? ☕"
msgstr "Wil jy dit interessanter maak? Probeer om potte en panne volgens grootte te sorteer: Kan hy/sy die klein pannetjies in die groter een pas?☕"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "If you are outside, name different kinds of vehicles on the street or things you see in nature like stones, sticks, trees and flowers. 🌷"
msgstr "As julle buite is, noem verskillende soorte voertuie in die straat, of goed wat jy in die natuur sien, soos klippe, bome en blomme. 🌷"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 You can play the categorising game anywhere! Just look around and ask your child to find things from the category you say!"
msgstr "🔄 Jy kan enige plek die kategoriseringspeletjie speel! Kyk rond en vra jou kind om goed te vind van die kategorie wat jy noem!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Sorting and grouping builds thinking skills, memory, and early logic -helping your child make sense of the world around them through playful discovery 🌈 "
msgstr "Sortering en groepering bou denkvaardighede, geheue en vroeë logika - dit help jou kind om sin te maak van die wêreld rondom hom/haar deur speelse ontdekking 🌈 "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Brain Building Through Play by Harvard University: https://developingchild.harvard.edu/resources/brainbuildingthroughplay/"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Brain Building Through Play by Harvard University: https://developingchild.harvard.edu/resources/brainbuildingthroughplay/"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Shapes Everywhere!*"
msgstr "*Vorms Waar jy Kyk!*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📺 Squares, squares everywhere"
msgstr "📺 Vierkante, vierkante waar jy kyk"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Draw squares in the sand or dirt. Make some bigger and some smaller."
msgstr "👀 Teken vierkante in die sand of grond. Maak party groter en ander kleiner."

#. type=text
#. Strings like @fields.xxx and @results.yyy should not be translated. 
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Tell @fields.child_nickname, “this is a square.” "
msgstr "Sê vir @fields.child_nickname, \"dit is 'n vierkant\".  "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Ask your child to try to draw a square. Hold your child’s hand to help if this is hard. "
msgstr "Vra vir jou kind om 'n vierkant te teken. Hou jou kind se hand vas om te help indien dit moeilik is."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Look for things around the home or outdoors that are the same shape."
msgstr "Kyk in die huis of buite vir goed wat dieselfde vorm het."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Now do the same with circles! 🔴"
msgstr "Doen nou dieselfde met sirkels! 🔴"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Tell your child, “this is a square.” "
msgstr "Sê vir jou kind, \"dit is 'n vierkant\". "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This simple shape game builds early maths skills, observation, and coordination - right from the start! ✅"
msgstr "Hierdie eenvoudige vormspel bou vroeë wiskundige vaardighede, waarneming en koördinasie - reg van die begin af! ✅"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Active Songs*"
msgstr "*Aktiewe Liedjies*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Young children love to move - and songs with actions make it even more fun! Singing gives your child cues for how and when to move 🎵"
msgstr "Jong kinders hou daarvan om te beweeg - liedjies met aksies maak dit meer pret! Sang gee jou kind tekens vir hoe en wanneer om te beweeg🎵"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Movement songs build listening skills, self-control, and rhythm - while helping your child learn to follow instructions!"
msgstr "Bewegingsliedjies bou luistervaardighede, selfvertroue en ritme - terwyl jou kind leer om instruksies te volg!"

#. type=text
#. Strings like @fields.xxx and @results.yyy should not be translated. 
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Sing songs to @fields.child_nickname or a group of children in which they have to:"
msgstr "Sing liedjies saam met @fields.child_nickname of 'n groep kinders waar hulle moet:"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "✅ Start and stop ❌"
msgstr "✅ Begin en stop ❌"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⬇️ Slow down and speed up ⬆️"
msgstr "⬇️ Stadiger en vinniger moet beweeg ⬆️"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Some song ideas:\r- “If you’re happy and you know it”\r- “Heads, shoulders, knees and toes”\r- “Freeze dance” (play or sing music and freeze when it stops!)\r- “Sleeping bunnies” (sleep, then hop!)"
msgstr "'n Paar liedjie-idees: \r- \"If you're happy and you know it\"\r- \"Kop, skouers, knieë en tone\"\r- \"Vriesdans\" (speel of sing liedjies en vries wanneer dit stop!)\r- \"Slapende hasies\"(slaap, dan hop!)"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Sing songs to your child or a group of children in which they have to:"
msgstr "Sing liedjies vir jou kinders of 'n groep kinders, waar hulle moet:"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Be the Narrator*"
msgstr "*Wees die Verteller*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Say what your child is doing while they are playing."
msgstr "👀 Sê wat jou kind besig is om te doen terwyl hy/sy speel."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂 This will help them learn the words to describe their actions."
msgstr "👂 Dit sal hulle help om die woorde te leer wat hulle aksies beskryf."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "😃 You can do it in a simple way, or in a silly way like a sports commentator, a news presenter, or a game show host."
msgstr "😃 Jy kan dit op 'n eenvoudige manier doen, of maak of jy 'n sportkommentator is, 'n nuusaanbieder of 'n speletjiesprogramaanbieder."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 Ask questions like “What will you do next?” or “I see you want to put the ball in the jar. Is there another way to do that?”"
msgstr "💡 Vra vrae soos \"Wat gaan jy volgende doen?\" of \"Ek sien jy wil die bal in die pot sit. Is daar n ander manier om dit te doen?\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Be an Artist!*"
msgstr "*Wees 'n Kunstenaar!*"

#. type=text
#. Strings like @fields.xxx and @results.yyy should not be translated. 
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📝 Give @fields.child_nickname some paper and a pen or pencil, or some different pens or pencils."
msgstr "📝 Gee vir @fields.child_nickname papier en 'n pen of potlood, of 'n paar verskillende penne of potlode."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "😃 Let your child draw whatever they want to!"
msgstr "😃 Laat jou kind teken net wat hy/sy wil!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Ask questions about what they are drawing, the size of the thing they are drawing, and the colours they are using."
msgstr "👀 Vra vrae oor wat hulle teken, die grootte van die ding wat hulle teken, en die kleure wat hulle gebruik."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🏆 If possible, put your child’s picture up on the wall when they are finished. Give praise to your child!"
msgstr "🏆 Indien moontlik, sit jou kind se prentjie teen die muur wanneer hy/sy klaar is. Prys jou kind!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📝 Give your child some paper and a pen or pencil, or some different pens or pencils."
msgstr "📝 Gee vir jou kind papier en 'n pen of potlood, of 'n paar verskillende penne of potlode."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This open drawing time builds imagination, fine motor skills, and confidence - especially when you celebrate their creations! 🎉"
msgstr "Hierdie ope tekentyd bou verbeelding, fyn motoriese vaardighede en selfvertroue - veral wanneer jy sy/haar ontwerpe vier! 🎉"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Echo Songs*"
msgstr "*Eggoliedjies*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "😃 Try a simple call-and-response chant with your child. You say a line, and they copy it back."
msgstr "😃 Probeer 'n eenvoudige roep-en-reageerliedjie met jou kind. Jy sê 'n reël, en jou kind sê dit terug."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂 For example:"
msgstr "👂 Byvoorbeeld:"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You: “Hello there!”"
msgstr "Jy: \"Hallo daar!\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Child: “Hello there!”"
msgstr "Kind: \"Hallo daar!\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You: “How are you?”"
msgstr "Jy: \"Hoe gaan dit?\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Child: “How are you?”"
msgstr "Kind: \"Hoe gaan dit?\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💚 Use your own words and language."
msgstr "💚 Gebruik jou eie woorde en taal."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "These traditional-style echo songs build turn-taking, memory, and early conversation skills - all through playful singing 🎵"
msgstr "Hierdie tradisionele styl eggoliedjies bou beurtneming, geheue en vroeë gesprekvoeringsvaardighede - alles deur prettig te sing 🎵"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Circle Clap and Dance*"
msgstr "*Klap en Dans in 'n Sirkel*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 Gather a few children (or just you and your little one) and form a small circle. "
msgstr "👋 Kry 'n paar kinders bymekaar (of net jy en jou kind) en vorm 'n klein sirkel. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This joyful game builds social confidence, movement skills, and musical rhythm - all while connecting to culture 💛"
msgstr "Hierdie jolige speletjie bou sosiale selfvertroue, bewegingsvaardighede en musikale ritme - alles terwyl hy/sy inskakel by 'n kultuur💛"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*One-on-One Time*"
msgstr "*Een-tot-Een Tyd*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💚 Spending time just with your child and taking an interest in them can improve your relationship."
msgstr "💚 Om tyd met jou kind te spandeer en belangstelling in hom/haar te toon, kan julle verhouding verbeter."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 When your child is playing alone or occupying themselves quietly, join them and show interest in what they are doing."
msgstr "👀 Wanneer jou kind alleen speel of hom-/haarself stilletjies besig hou, sluit by hom/haar aan en wys belangstelling in wat hy/sy doen."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂Ask questions about their activity, and listen to them."
msgstr "👂Vra vrae oor hulle aktiwiteit, en luister na hulle."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let your child lead the activity, follow them to build their confidence and autonomy 😃."
msgstr "Laat jou kind die aktiwiteit lei, volg hom/haar om sy/haar selfvertroue en individualiteit te bou 😀."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Say what you see - describing everything and supporting your child’s actions."
msgstr "👀 Sê wat jy sien - beskryf alles en ondersteun jou kind se aksies."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Be positive, praise your child, and enjoy spending this time with them 😃💚"
msgstr "Wees positief, prys jou kind en geniet die tyd saam met hom/haar😀💚"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📖 Book sharing will help your child learn and is a fun, playful activity to spend quality time together."
msgstr "📖 Saamlees sal jou kind help om te leer, en dis 'n prettige speelaktiwiteit om kwaliteittyd saam te spandeer."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⏰ Choose a time when you won’t be disturbed, and try to stop any distractions - e.g. turn off the TV and put away phones."
msgstr "⏰ Kies 'n tyd wanneer julle nie onderbreek sal word nie, en probeer om enige afleidings te stop - bv. skakel die TV af en bêre alle fone."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📖 If your child wants to choose a book, that’s fine, otherwise choose for them."
msgstr "📖 As jou kind 'n boekie wil kies, is dit reg, andersins kies jy vir hom/haar."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💚 Sit close together and follow your child’s attention and lead. "
msgstr "💚 Sit na aan mekaar en volg jou kind se aandag en leiding. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Point at things, name and repeat words. Help them to learn more about what interests them in the book 👀 "
msgstr "Wys na dinge, benoem dit en herhaal woorde. Help hulle om meer te leer oor dit wat hulle interesseer in die boek 👀 "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Link things in the books to your child's life, and use words about emotions and talk about them! 😃"
msgstr "Verbind dinge in die boeke aan jou kind se lewe, en gebruik woorde oor emosies en praat daaroor! 😃"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 If possible, start a regular routine to read together when your child isn’t too tired or hungry."
msgstr "🔄 Indien moontlik, begin 'n gereelde roetine om saam te lees, wanneer jou kind nie te moeg of honger is nie."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Reading together is one of the best ways to help your child learn and prepare for success in school! 🎓"
msgstr "Om saam te lees is een van die beste maniere om jou kind te help leer en voor te berei vir sukses in die skool! 🎓"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💚 Sit close together and follow your child's attention and lead. "
msgstr "💚 Sit na aan mekaar en volg jou kind se aandag en leiding. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "If there are words or numbers in the book, ask and help your child recognise letters numbers, and simple words 💡. "
msgstr "As daar woorde of getalle in die boek is, vra jou kind en help hom/haar om letters, getalle en eenvoudige woorde te herken 💡 "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Link things in the books to your child's life, and use words about emotions and talk about them! 😃."
msgstr "Verbind dinge in die boeke aan jou kind se lewe, en gebruik woorde oor emosies en praat daaroor! 😃."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Animal Acting*"
msgstr "* Diere-Aksie*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Get ready to roar like a lion or hop like a kangaroo! 🧸"
msgstr "Maak gereed om soos 'n leeu te brul of soos 'n kangaroe te hop! 🧸"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📝 To start, write the names of animals on small pieces of paper and put them in a box or container."
msgstr "📝 Om te begin, skryf die name van die diere op 'n stukkie papier en sit dit in 'n leë houer."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 Take turns picking a piece of paper and acting out the animal - can you mimic its sounds and movements? Roar, jump, crawl, or fly just like the animal you picked!"
msgstr "👋 Maak beurte om 'n stukkie papier uit te haal en te reageer soos die spesifieke dier - kan jy die geluide en bewegings naboots? Brul, spring, kruip of vlieg soos die dier wat jy gekies het!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎉 For older kids, turn it into a fun guessing game - see if others can guess which animal you’re pretending to be!"
msgstr "🎉 Vir ouer kinders, verander dit in 'n prettige raai-raai-speletjie - kyk of hulle kan raai watter dier jy namaak!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This active game helps kids develop physical skills while also supporting speech and language development in a fun way 💚"
msgstr "Hierdie aktiewe speletjie help om kinders fisies te ontwikkel, terwyl hulle spraak en taal op 'n prettige manier ontwikkel word 💚"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Freeze Dance*"
msgstr "*Vriesdans*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Get ready to dance and freeze with this exciting activity that toddlers love! 🎵"
msgstr "Maak gereed om te dans en te vries met hierdie opwindende aktiwiteit waarvan kleuters baie hou! 🎵"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📻 Play some music and let your child dance or move however they like. "
msgstr "📻 Speel musiek en laat jou kind dans en beweeg net soos hy/sy wil. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⏸ When the music stops, tell them to freeze – to not move at all! – in one place."
msgstr "⏸ Wanneer die musiek stop, sê vir hom/haar om te vries - om glad nie te beweeg nie - op een plek."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This fun game is great for building listening skills and self-control as they practise stopping and starting ✨ "
msgstr "Hierdie prettige speletjie help met jou kind se luistervaardighede en selfbeheersing, soos hy/sy oefen om te stop en weer te begin ✨ "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "It’s also a wonderful way to prepare for school, where they’ll need to follow directions 🔑 "
msgstr "Dis ook 'n goeie manier om hom/haar voor te berei vir skool, waar hy/sy aanwysings moet volg 🔑 "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "So, turn up the music and enjoy the dancing – and the freezing! 💚"
msgstr "So, sit die musiek harder en geniet die dans - en die vries! 💚"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Mystery Bag*"
msgstr "*Raaiselsak*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This game is easy and perfect for engaging your toddler’s senses and learning new words 🎁"
msgstr "Hierdie speletjie is maklik en perfek om jou kleuter se sintuie te betrek en om nuwe woorde te leer 🎁"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🏆 Simply place different objects into a bag and ask your child to reach in, feel an item, and guess what it is before pulling it out. "
msgstr "🏆 Plaas verskillende voorwerpe in 'n sak en vra jou kind om 'n item te voel en te raai wat dit is voordat hy/sy dit uithaal. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 When they pull out the item, ask them questions to describe what they see: Is it smooth or scary? Bumpy or bright?"
msgstr "👋 Wanneer hy/sy die item uithaal, vra vir hom/haar vrae om te beskryf wat hy/sy sien: Is dit glad of grillerig? Hobbelrig of helder?"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "It’s a fun way to introduce new words and stimulate their sense of touch! 💡"
msgstr "Dis 'n prettige manier om nuwe woorde bekend te stel en sy/haar tassintuig te stimuleer! 💡"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Benefits of this activity include expanding vocabulary, developing tactile senses, and practising grouping skills. It’s a wonderful way to mix fun with learning! 🎉"
msgstr "Voordele van hierdie aktiwiteit sluit die uitbreiding van sy/haar woordeskat in, asook ontwikkeling van die tassintuig en om groeperingsvaardighede te oefen. Dis 'n wonderlike manier om pret met leer te meng! 🎉"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from British Council: https://learnenglishkids.britishcouncil.org/parents/top-tips/mystery-bag-game"
msgstr "Aangepas uit British Council: https://learnenglishkids.britishcouncil.org/parents/top-tips/mystery-bag-game"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Body Outline*"
msgstr "*Buitelyn van die Liggaam*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This fun and interactive game helps your toddler learn about different parts of the body 🧸"
msgstr "Hierdie prettige interaktiewe speletjie help jou kleuter leer van die verskillende dele van die liggaam 🧸"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📝 Start by drawing their body outline on a large piece of paper or with a stick on the ground. "
msgstr "📝 Begin deur die buitelyn van sy/haar liggaam op 'n groot stuk papier te teken, of met 'n stok op die grond. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂 As you go, ask them to point to and name different body parts. For example, you can say, “Where’s your nose?” or “Can you point to your feet?” "
msgstr "👂 Soos jy aangaan, vra hom/haar om die verskillende liggaamsdele te wys en te noem. Jy kan byvoorbeeld sê, \"Waar is jou neus?\" of \"Kan jy na sy voete wys?\" "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋As they point, encourage them to name each part. "
msgstr "👋 Soos hy/sy wys, moedig hom/haar aan om elke deel te noem. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎨 When you are done, you can colour in the outline or decorate it with anything you have in or around the house to make it more creative and engaging!"
msgstr "🎨 Wanneer julle klaar is, kan julle die buitelyn inkleur of versier met enigiets wat julle in of rondom die huis het om dit meer kreatief te maak!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This fun and creative activity helps your child improve their body awareness, learn new words, and develop fine motor skills 💡"
msgstr "Hierdie prettige en kreatiewe aktiwiteit help jou kind om die bewustheid van sy/haar liggaam te verbeter, nuwe woorde te leer en fyn motoriese vaardighede te ontwikkel 💡"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Paper Ball Game*"
msgstr "*Papierbal-Speletjie*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Get ready to practice your child’s aim and physical coordination as you play with paper balls together 🔷"
msgstr "Maak gereed om jou kind se akkuraatheidsvernuf en fisiese koördinasie te oefen terwyl julle saam met die papierballe speel 🔷"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📝 Here’s what you’ll need: paper (to scrunch up into balls), and crayons."
msgstr "📝 Hier is wat jy sal benodig: papier (om in balle op te frommel) en kryt."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎨 Start by colouring each piece of paper so that it is a unique colour. Now scrunch up the paper until you have a paper ball."
msgstr "🎨 Begin deur elke deel van die papier in te kleur sodat dit 'n unieke kleur is. Frommel nou die papier op tot jy 'n papierbal het."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🚩 Next, make a goal. You can use markings that already exist, or a clear table surface."
msgstr "🚩 Volgende, maak 'n doel. Gebruik merke wat alreeds bestaan, of gebruik 'n skoon oppervlak."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🏅 Now you’re ready to play! Take turns tossing your ball towards the goal. Whoever scores or lands closest to the goal wins the round!"
msgstr "🏅 Nou is jy gereed om te speel! Maak beurte om die bal na die doel te gooi. Wie ook al die papierbal die naaste aan die doel plaas, wen die rondte!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This fun and engaging game is perfect for boosting your child’s physical coordination and decision-making skills while keeping them entertained. Let the friendly competition begin! ⭐"
msgstr "Hierdie prettige interaktiewe speletjie is perfek om jou kind se fisiese koördinasie en besluitnemingsvaardighede te verbeter terwyl hy/sy vermaak word. Laat die vriendskaplike kompetisie begin!⭐"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/jumping-caps"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/jumping-caps"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Letter in the Shop*"
msgstr "*Briefie in die Winkel*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Turn your next trip to the store into a learning adventure! 🍞"
msgstr "Omskep jou volgende uitstappie na die winkel in 'n leeravontuur! 🍞"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🍅 As you shop, pick a letter and talk about the items on your shopping list that start with that letter. "
msgstr "🍅 Terwyl julle inkopies doen, kies 'n letter en praat oor die item op jou inkopielys wat met dieselfde letter begin. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Ask your child to find other things in the shop that start with the same letter."
msgstr "👀 Vra jou kind om nog items wat met dieselfde letter begin, in die winkel te vind."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This simple activity helps build your child’s letter recognition and vocabulary while keeping them engaged during the shopping trip ✨"
msgstr "Hierdie eenvoudige aktiwiteit help om jou kind se letterherkenning en woordeskat te bou terwyl jy hom/haar betrokke maak by die inkopie-uitstappie ✨"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "It’s a fun, interactive way to learn about letters and sounds in real-world situations, turning an ordinary task into an exciting educational game! 🌈"
msgstr "Dis 'n prettige interaktiewe manier om in die regte wêreld oor letters en geluide te leer deur 'n eenvoudige taak in 'n opwindende opvoedkundige speletjie te omskep! 🌈"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Sesame Workshop: https://sesameworkshop.org/resources/what-will-we-do/"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Sesame Workshop: https://sesameworkshop.org/resources/what-will-we-do/"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Fun with Food*"
msgstr "*Pret met Kos*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Cooking can help your child start learning maths!"
msgstr "Kosmaak kan jou kind help om wiskunde te leer!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💚 Invite your child to help you cook for your family, or to help you prepare a colourful fruit salad."
msgstr "💚 Nooi jou kind om jou te help om vir die gesin te kook, of om jou te help om 'n kleurvolle vrugteslaai voor te berei."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🍅 As you gather the ingredients, ask them to count: 'How many tomatoes do we have?' This builds maths skills and encourages teamwork."
msgstr "🍅 Soos jy die bestanddele bymekaar maak, vra jou kind om dit te tel: \"Hoeveel tamaties is daar?\" Dit bou wiskundige vaardighede en moedig spanwerk aan."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "5️⃣ Help your child to understand adding and subtracting quantities. 'We need five tomatoes, if we have three, how many more do we need?' This makes learning fun!"
msgstr "5️⃣ Help jou kind om optel en aftrek van hoeveelhede te verstaan. \"Ons het vyf tamaties nodig. As ons drie het, hoeveel het ons nog nodig?\" Dit maak leer pret!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Let’s make it playful! Ask, 'Which is bigger: the tomato or the onion?' This reinforces comparison skills."
msgstr "👀 Kom ons maak dit speel-speel! \"Wat is die grootste, die tamatie of die ui?\" Dit versterk vergelykingsvaardighede."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Consider planning a weekly cooking night. "
msgstr "🔄 Oorweeg dit om 'n weeklikse kookaand te beplan. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Cooking strengthens your relationship and builds your child’s confidence. Enjoy your cooking adventure together!"
msgstr "Om saam te kook, maak jul verhouding sterker en dit bou die kind se selfvertroue. Geniet julle kookavonture saam!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Thrive By Five: https://www.thrivebyfive.com/"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Thrive By Five: https://www.thrivebyfive.com/"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Following Instructions*"
msgstr "*Volg Instruksies*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂 Play a game in which your child listens to and tries to remember strings of instructions."
msgstr "👂 Speel 'n speletjie waar jou kind luister en probeer om veelvuldige instruksies te onthou."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This will be useful in school, at home, and later in life!"
msgstr "Dit sal op skool, tuis, en later in die lewe handig te pas kom!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Start with just one instruction using an object in your home. For example “touch the red ball” 🔴"
msgstr "Begin met slegs een instruksie deur 'n voorwerp in julle huis te gebruik, byvoorbeeld “raak aan die rooi bal”. 🔴"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Slowly add more instructions (e.g “then pick up the cup \"☕), but tell your child that they can only start once you’ve finished giving the instructions."
msgstr "Voeg meer instruksies geleidelik by (bv. \"tel dan die koppie op\"☕), maar sê vir jou kind dat hy/sy slegs kan begin nadat jy die instruksies gegee het."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "See how many your child can follow without forgetting!"
msgstr "Kyk hoeveel instruksies jou kind kan volg sonder om te vergeet!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Now swap roles! It’s your child’s turn to give you instructions! They can use the same objects if they want."
msgstr "🔄 Ruil nou rolle om! Dis jou kind se beurt om vir jou instruksies te gee! Hy/sy kan dieselfde voorwerpe gebruik as hy/sy wil."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You can also try this game with a group of children! Make sure they take turns 😃"
msgstr "Jy kan ook hierdie speletjie met 'n groep kinders probeer! Maak seker dat hulle beurte maak 😃"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*I Spy Colours!*"
msgstr "* Ek Sien Kleure!*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Choose an object around you and say: “I spy with my little eye, something that is…” and say the colour of object, like “yellow” or “red”. "
msgstr "👀 Kies 'n voorwerp naby jou en sê: \"Ek sien met my kleine ogie, iets wat ... is.\" Sê die kleur van die voorwerp, soos \"geel\" of \"rooi\". "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "✅ Encourage your child to look around and guess what the object might be. When they guess correctly, give them praise and switch roles! "
msgstr "✅ Moedig jou kind aan om rond te kyk en te raai wat die voorwerp kan wees. Wanneer hy/sy reg raai, prys hom/haar en ruil rolle om! "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔑 If they’re having trouble, offer clues like, “It’s round” or “It’s somewhere in that corner\"."
msgstr "🔑 As hy/sy dit moeilik vind, gee leidrade soos \"dis rond\" of \"dis iewers in daardie hoek\"."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Keep the game going with new objects and different colours."
msgstr "🔄 Hou aan met die speletjie deur nuwe voorwerpe en verskillende kleure te gebruik."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This classic game is a fun and interactive way to help your child learn words, observe, and stay concentrated. This will help them at home and in school 🏁"
msgstr "Hierdie klassieke speletjie is 'n prettige en interaktiewe manier om jou kind woorde, waarneming en konsentrasie te leer. Dit sal hom/haar by die huis en by die skool help 🏁"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*I Spy Letters!*"
msgstr "*Ek Sien Letters!*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 I spy is a fun game to play with your child that will help them learn about letters and words!"
msgstr "👀 \"Ek sien\" is 'n lekker speletjie om met jou kind te speel, en dit help hom/haar om letters en woorde te leer!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Choose an object or a thing around you, and don’t tell your child what it is. It should be something that your child knows the word for. For example “ball” ⚽"
msgstr "Kies 'n voorwerp of iets naby jou, en moenie vir jou kind sê wat dit is nie. Dit moet 'n eenvoudige voorwerp wees wat jou kind ken, bv. \"bal\" ⚽"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Then say “I spy with my little eye, something beginning with *and then say the first letter of the word* which in this case is “b”"
msgstr "👀 Sê dan “Ek sien met my kleine ogie, iets wat begin met *en sê dan die eerste letter van die woord,* wat in hierdie geval “b” is"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Your child should look around and guess what the object is. When they guess it right, praise them and swap roles! If they can’t get it, give them some clues, like “it’s round” or “it’s black and white”. ✅"
msgstr "Jou kind moet rondkyk en raai wat die voorwerp is. Wanneer hy/sy reg raai, prys hom/haar en ruil rolle om. As hy/sy nie dit nie regkry nie, gee leidrade soos \"dis rond\" of \"dis wit en swart\". ✅"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Play this game with as many objects as possible and as many different letters! Help your child to learn about the different letters and sounds in words. This will help them learn to read at home and school. 🎓"
msgstr "Speel hierdie speletjie met soveel voorwerpe as moontlik en baie verskillende letters! Help jou kind om van die verskillende letters en klanke in woorde te leer. Dit sal hom/haar by die huis en by die skool help om te leer lees. 🎓"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*What Letter is This?*"
msgstr "*Watter Letter is Dit?*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Playing games with letters can help your child learn the alphabet and how letters are put together to make words."
msgstr "Speletjies met letters kan jou kind help om die alfabet te leer en hoe letters bymekaargesit word om woorde te vorm."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📝 Write a letter on a piece of card or paper (e.g. “p”)"
msgstr "📝 Skryf 'n letter op 'n stukkie karton of papier (bv. “p”)"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂 Say the letter out loud and ask your child to say it too!"
msgstr "👂 Sê die letter hardop en vra jou kind om dit ook te sê!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Ask your child to say some words that begin with the letter “p”, give them clues like “What starts with “p”? Plant… What else? 🌱"
msgstr "Vra jou kind om 'n paar woorde te noem wat met die letter \"p\" begin; gee vir hom/haar leidrade soos \"Wat begin met P?\" Plant ... Wat nog? 🌱"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Ask your child to look for objects in your house that begin with a letter (eg “p” for plate). Help them find things."
msgstr "👀 Vra vir jou kind om voorwerpe in die huis te soek wat met 'n sekere letter begin (bv. \"b\" vir bord). Help hom/haar om die goed te vind."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Try a new letter every day!"
msgstr "🔄 Probeer elke dag 'n nuwe letter!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Riddles Time*"
msgstr "*Raaiseltyd*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Riddles and puzzles are a fun way to build thinking skills! 💡"
msgstr "Raaisels en kopkrappers is 'n prettige manier om denkvaardighede te ontwikkel! 💡"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Do you remember any riddles from your childhood? If you can’t then make one up, they can be very simple! 😃"
msgstr "Onthou jy enige raaisels uit jou kinderdae? As jy nie kan nie, dink dan een uit, dit kan baie eenvoudig wees! 😃"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Like “What can you see at night but not in the day” Answer: “The moon” 🌙"
msgstr "Soos “Wat kan jy in die nag sien, maar nie in die dag nie?” Antwoord: “Die maan” 🌙"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "If your child is finding them difficult, try an easy one like: “What is round, bouncy and can be thrown or kicked?” Answer: “A ball” ⚽"
msgstr "As jou kind dit moeilik vind, probeer 'n makliker een soos: \"Wat is rond, hop en kan gegooi of geskop word?\" Antwoord: \"'n Bal\" ⚽"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Your child can also try making riddles! 💡"
msgstr "Jou kind kan ook probeer om self raaisels te maak! 💡"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You can have fun with riddles anywhere at any time - like traveling on a bus, walking to school or in a car 🚗"
msgstr "Julle kan enige plek, enige tyd, pret met raaisels hê - soos terwyl julle in 'n bus ry, skool toe stap of in 'n motor ry 🚗"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Make up a Story*"
msgstr "*Dink 'n Storie uit*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Creating stories together is a great way to have fun with imagination - and to build your child’s creativity! 📖"
msgstr "Om stories te skep, is 'n goeie manier om pret met verbeelding te hê - en om jou kind se kreatiwiteit te ontwikkel! 📖"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "5️⃣ With your child, come up with 5 words to use. They can be any words you want! For example: banana, spaceship, fish, water, painting, cooking, wedding. If you need to remember them, write them clearly on a paper with your child."
msgstr "5️⃣ Dink, saam met jou kind, aan 5 woorde om te gebruik. Dit kan enige woorde wees! Byvoorbeeld: piesang, ruimteskip, vis, water, skildery, kook, troue. As julle dit moet onthou, skryf dit duidelik op 'n stukkie papier saam met jou kind neer."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎂 Start your story with, “Once upon a time, there was a…” and use one of the words from the list in the first part. For example, “Once upon a time, there was a family who worked on a *banana* farm.”"
msgstr "🎂 Begin julle storie met “Eendag, lank, lank gelede was daar 'n …” en gebruik een van die woorde uit die lys in die eerste deel. Byvoorbeeld, “Eendag, lank, lank gelede was daar 'n gesin wat op 'n *piesang*-plaas gewerk het.”"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📝 Let your child make up the next part using another word from the list."
msgstr "📝 Laat jou kind die volgende gedeelte doen, deur 'n ander woord op die lys te gebruik."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Take turns until you have used all the words and created a story. "
msgstr "🔄 Neem beurte totdat julle al die woorde gebruik het en 'n storie geskep het. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔔 Be creative and do not tell your child what to say. It does not need to be a real story to be fun!"
msgstr "🔔 Wees kreatief en moenie vir jou kind sê wat om te sê nie. Dit het nie nodig om 'n ware storie te wees om pret te wees nie!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎁 Ask your child what their favourite part of the story was, and tell them yours!"
msgstr "🎁 Vra wat sy/haar gunstelingdeel van die storie was en noem ook jou gunstelingdeel!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Playing with Clothes*"
msgstr "*Speel met Klere*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 Clothes can be the perfect ‘toys’ to help your child build fine motor skills, recognise colours, and think! Here are 3 ideas you can try:"
msgstr "💡 Klere kan die perfekte speelgoed wees om fyn motoriese vaardighede te bou, kleure te herken en te dink! Hier is 3 idees wat jy kan probeer:"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 Practice "
msgstr "👋 Oefen "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Help your child exercise their fingers by showing them how buttons and zips work on clothes, and letting them practise using them!"
msgstr "Help jou kind om sy/haar vingers te oefen deur te wys hoe knope en ritssluiters aan klere werk en laat hy/sy oefen om dit te gebruik!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔵 Colours"
msgstr "🔵 Kleure"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Talk about the colours of clothes! Ask your child to name the colours of their clothes and talk about all the things that are that colour: “What are all the things we can think of that are blue?”"
msgstr "Gesels oor die kleure van klere! Vra vir jou kind om die kleure van sy/haar klere te noem en praat oor goed wat daardie kleur is: \"Aan watter goed kan ons alles dink wat blou is?\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔶 Sorting"
msgstr "🔶 Sortering"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "When you have done laundry, ask your child to help you sort clothes into piles for each family member."
msgstr "Wanneer jy wasgoed gewas het, vra jou kind om jou te help om die wasgoed uit te sorteer, met 'n hoop vir elke gesinslid."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Playing with Vegetables*"
msgstr "*Speel met Groente*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🌱 Help your child learn by thinking and talking about vegetables! Here are 3 ideas for you:"
msgstr "🌱 Help jou kind om te leer deur te dink en te praat oor groente! Hier is 3 idees vir jou:"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🍅 Sorting vegetables\rMix together 2-3 different ingredients of your choice (like onions, tomatoes and corn example). Say: “Help me sort these vegetables into piles?” Try sorting them by size."
msgstr "🍅 Sortering van groente\rMeng 2-3 verskillende bestanddele van jou keuse saam (soos byvoorbeeld uie, tamaties en mielies). Sê: \"Kom ons sorteer hierdie groente in hopies.\" Probeer om hulle volgens grootte te sorteer."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "😃 Remind me!"
msgstr "😃 Herinner my!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Talk about your child’s experiences. Ask questions and wait for answers. Follow your child’s interests. "
msgstr "Praat oor jou kind se ervarings. Vra vrae en wag vir antwoorde. Volg jou kind se belangstellings. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "“Can you help me remember what is at the market?” “Do they sell carrots at the market?” “Do they sell anything yellow at the market?” “What else do they sell?”"
msgstr "\"Kan jy my help om te onthou wat by die mark is?\" \"Verkoop hulle wortels by die mark?\" \"Verkoop hulle enige geel goed by die mark?\" \"Wat verkoop hulle nog?\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 Something similar"
msgstr "💡 Iets Soortgelyks"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Say: We are going to think of some things that are similar or different from what I tell you. So listen carefully!”"
msgstr "Sê: \"Ons gaan dink aan goed wat dieselfde of verskillend is van wat ek vir jou sê. So luister mooi!”"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Here is a tomato. Can you think of something else that is red like a tomato? 🍅"
msgstr "Hier is 'n tamatie. Kan jy aan nog iets dink wat rooi is soos 'n tamatie? 🍅"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Can you think of something else that is round like a tomato? ⚽"
msgstr "Kan jy aan nog iets dink wat rond is soos 'n tamatie? ⚽"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "These fun food games build memory, observation, and language - helping your child compare, recall, and explore the world through everyday things 🏆"
msgstr "Hierdie lekker kosspeletjies bou geheue, waarneming en taal - dit help jou kind om vergelykings te maak, te herroep en die wêreld te verken deur alledaagse dinge 🏆"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Animals*"
msgstr "*Diere*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Here are 3 fun animal-related games you can play! "
msgstr "Hier is 3 prettige diereverwante speletjies wat julle kan speel! "

#. type=text
#. Strings like @fields.xxx and @results.yyy should not be translated. 
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🧸 Active animals \rTake turns with @fields.child_nickname doing animal actions: Hop like a frog, stretch like a cat, run like a dog, slither like a snake, flap like a bird."
msgstr "🧸 Aktiewe diere \rMaak beurte met @fields.child_nickname om diere-aksies te doen: Hop soos 'n padda, strek soos 'n kat, hardloop soos 'n hond, seil soos 'n slang, flap soos 'n voël."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🧸 Active animals \rTake turns with your child doing animal actions: Hop like a frog, stretch like a cat, run like a dog, slither like a snake, flap like a bird."
msgstr "🧸 Aktiewe diere \r Maak beurte met jou kind om diere-aksies te doen: Hop soos 'n padda, strek soos 'n kat, hardloop soos 'n hond, seil soos 'n slang, flap soos 'n voël."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 Groups of animals"
msgstr "💡 Groepe diere"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "What are all the animals we can think of that have feathers?"
msgstr "Aan watter diere kan ons almal dink wat vere het?"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "What are all the animals we can think of that eat plants? 🌱"
msgstr "Aan watter diere kan ons almal dink wat plante eet? 🌱"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "What are all the animals we can think of that lay eggs?"
msgstr "Aan watter diere kan ons almal dink wat eiers lê?"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "😃 Counting rabbits"
msgstr "😃 Tel hasies!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔟 Find 10 rocks and tell your child that they are rabbits!"
msgstr "🔟 Vind 10 klippe en sê vir jou kind dat hulle hasies is!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Put them in a line and ask them to count the rabbits."
msgstr "Sit hulle in 'n ry en vra hom/haar om die hasies te tel."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Ask your child to give you 3 rabbits. Say “If you give me 3, how many rabbits do you have?”"
msgstr "Vra jou kind om vir jou 3 hasies te gee. Sê: \"As jy vir my 3 gee, hoeveel hasies gaan jy dan hê?\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "These playful animal games build movement, counting, and thinking skills - while sparking your child’s curiosity about the natural world 🌈"
msgstr "Hierdie prettige dierespeletjies bevorder beweging, tel en denkvaardighede - terwyl jy jou kind se nuuskierigheid oor die natuur aanwakker 🌈"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Active Counting*"
msgstr "*Tel Aktief*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Here are 2 fun games that help your child learn how to count, listen, and remember!"
msgstr "Hier is 2 prettige speletjies wat jou kind leer om te tel, luister en onthou!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 Clap, hop, jump: "
msgstr "👋 Klap, hop, spring: "

#. type=text
#. Strings like @fields.xxx and @results.yyy should not be translated. 
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Play the following game with @fields.child_nickname. Make it active!"
msgstr "Speel die volgende speletjie met @fields.child_nickname. Maak dit aktief!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "1️⃣ Clap hands 1 time. 2️⃣ Clap hands 2 times."
msgstr "1️⃣ Klap hande 1 keer. 2️⃣ Klap hande 2 keer."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "1️⃣ Jump 1 time. 2️⃣ Jump 2 times."
msgstr "1️⃣ Spring 1 keer. 2️⃣ Spring 2 keer."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "1️⃣ Hop 1 time. 3️⃣ Hop 3 times."
msgstr "1️⃣ Hop 1 keer. 3️⃣ Hop 3 keer."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 Can you hop, then jump, then clap? "
msgstr "💡 Kan jy hop, dan spring, dan klap? "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🏆 Can you clap twice, jump once, and hop three times?"
msgstr "🏆 Kan jy twee keer klap, een keer spring en drie keer huppel?"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Play the following game with your child. Make it active!"
msgstr "Speel die volgende speletjie met jou kind. Maak dit aktief!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 Remembering Instructions"
msgstr "💡 Om Instruksies te Onthou"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Take turns to give 2-3 instructions that the other person has to follow. Make sure physical movement is included!"
msgstr "Maak beurte om 2-3 instruksies te gee wat die ander persoon moet volg. Maak seker dat fisiese beweging ingesluit is!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "For example:"
msgstr "Byvoorbeeld:"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "- Hop twice, then turn around."
msgstr "- Hop twee keer, draai dan om."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "- Jump to the kitchen, pick up a spoon, then run back. ✅"
msgstr "- Spring na die kombuis, tel 'n lepel op en hardloop dan terug. ✅"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "These active games builds memory, coordination, and listening skills - helping your child follow instructions while moving their body 👋"
msgstr "Hierdie aktiewe speletjie bou geheue, koördinasie en luistervaardighede - dit help jou kind om instruksies te volg terwyl hy/sy sy/haar liggaampie beweeg 👋"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Thinking Games*"
msgstr "*Dinkspeletjies*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let’s play some games to help your child think and follow instructions!"
msgstr "Speel speletjies wat jou kind help om te dink en instruksies te volg!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "❗ Mama/Daddy says! "
msgstr "❗ Mamma/Pappa se! "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Give your child brief instructions to follow, by saying: “Mama/daddy says… touch your head”. "
msgstr "Gee kort instruksies aan jou kind om te volg, deur te sê: \"Mamma/Pappa sê ... vat aan jou kop\". "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "“Mama/daddy says… jump twice”. "
msgstr "\"Mamma/Pappa sê ... spring twee keer\" "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Once your child understands the game well, you can make it more complicated!"
msgstr "Sodra jou kind die spel goed verstaan, kan jy dit meer ingewikkeld maak!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "“Mama/daddy says… jump, then clap and sit”."
msgstr "“Mamma/pappa sê… spring, klap dan en sit”."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔵 🔴 Blue-Red "
msgstr "🔵 🔴 Blou-Rooi "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Say a colour, and your child needs to quickly find and touch something of that colour."
msgstr "Sê 'n kleur, dan moet jou kind vinnig aan iets raak wat dieselfde kleur is."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "To make the game harder, you can choose two colours and tell your child they should touch the opposite colour!"
msgstr "Om die speletjie moeiliker te maak, kan jy twee kleure kies en vir jou kind sê om aan die teenoorgestelde kleur te raak!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "“If I say blue, you should touch something red. If I say red, you need to touch something blue.”"
msgstr "\"As ek blou sê, moet jy aan iets rooi vat. As ek rooi sê, moet jy aan iets blou vat\"."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Try these games to help your child build listening skills, follow instructions, and have fun - all at the same time!"
msgstr "Probeer hierdie speletjies om jou kind te help met luistervaardighede, om instruksies uit te voer en pret te hê - alles op dieselfde tyd!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂 Go and stop "
msgstr "👂 Gaan en stop "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Say: When I say “stop”, we freeze. When I say “go”, we can walk again."
msgstr "Sê: Wanneer ek sê “stop”, vries ons. Wanneer ek sê “gaan”, kan ons weer loop."

#. type=text
#. Strings like @fields.xxx and @results.yyy should not be translated. 
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Once @fields.child_nickname is familiar with the game, @fields.child_nickname will lead."
msgstr "Wanneer @fields.child_nickname die speletjie ken, sal @fields.child_nickname die leiding neem."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Once your child is familiar with the game, your child will lead."
msgstr "Wanneer jou kind die speletjie ken, sal jou kind die leiding neem."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Games with Pictures!*"
msgstr "*Speletjies met Prente!*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Any picture or image can turn into a game:"
msgstr "Enige prentjie of beeld kan in 'n speletjie verander:"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂 Making up a story"
msgstr "👂 Maak 'n storie op"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Find a picture with people or animals in an old newspaper, book, or magazine, or on packaging. "
msgstr "Kry 'n prentjie met mense of diere in 'n ou koerant, boek, tydskrif, of op verpakking. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Say: “Let’s make up a story about this picture. I can start. This little girl is feeling very excited today. Why do you think she is feeling excited?”"
msgstr "Sê: \"Kom ons maak ons eie storie met die prentjie. Ek kan begin. Hierdie dogtertjie voel vandag baie opgewonde. Hoekom dink jy is sy so opgewonde?\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "😃 “She is holding her bag and has a big smile. Where do you think she is going?”"
msgstr "😃 \"Sy hou haar sak vas met 'n groot glimlag. Waar dink jy gaan sy heen?\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Can you guess it?"
msgstr "👀 Kan jy raai?"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Say: “I am going to describe something on the page and you need to guess what it is and point to it”. For example, “I see something that is green and moves slowly."
msgstr "Sê: \"Ek gaan iets op die prentjie beskryf en jy moet raai wat dit is en daarna wys.\" Byvoorbeeld: \"Ek sien iets wat groen is en dit beweeg stadig.\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Can you guess what it is?” 💚"
msgstr "Kan jy raai wat dit is?” 💚"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "These playful games build imagination, language, and thinking skills - while helping your child listen and express their own ideas in a fun way 💡"
msgstr "Hierdie prettige speletjies bou verbeelding, taal en denkvaardighede - terwyl dit jou kind help om te luister en sy/haar eie idees op 'n prettige manier uit te druk 💡"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Tell Me a Story!*"
msgstr "*Vertel vir My 'n Storie!*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂 Sit together in a cosy spot and begin a story the traditional way in your home language, like “Once upon a time...”"
msgstr "👂 Sit saam op 'n snoesige plek en begin deur jou storie op die tradisionele manier in jou moedertaal te vertel, soos \"Eendag, lank, lank gelede ...\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "✨ Use your voice, hands, and expressions to bring the story to life. It could be about animals, a clever child, or a talking tree! Let your child add sounds or repeat words. You can even ask them what happens next!"
msgstr "✨ Gebruik jou stem, hande en uitdrukkings om die storie lewe te gee. Dit moet gaan oor diere, 'n slim kind of 'n boom wat kan praat! Laat jou kind klanke byvoeg en woorde herhaal. Jy kan hulle selfs vra wat volgende gebeur!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 Traditional storytelling builds language, imagination, and cultural identity - and creates beautiful quiet time together."
msgstr "💡 Tradisionele stories bou taal, verbeelding en kulturele identiteit - en skep wonderlike stiltetyd saam."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Proverb Play*"
msgstr "*Spreekwoordespel*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let’s bring wisdom to life through play! ✨"
msgstr "Kweek lewenswysheid deur speel! ✨"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🌱 Think of a traditional proverb and act it out together. Pretend to be the animal or act out the scenario of the proverb - use movement, voices, and imagination!"
msgstr "🌱 Dink aan 'n tradisionele spreekwoord en voer dit saam uit. Maak of jy die dier is of voer die spreekwoord uit - gebruik beweging. stemme en verbeelding!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📖 Here are some ideas to get you started:"
msgstr "📖 Hier is 'n paar idees om jou aan die gang te kry:"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "- “Even an ant can hurt an elephant” - Pretend to be a big stomping elephant, then tiny ants that tickle its feet!"
msgstr "- \"Selfs 'n mier kan 'n olifant seermaak\" - Maak of jy 'n grootpoot-olifant is, dan miertjies wat die olifant se pote kielie!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "- “The lion doesn’t turn around when a small dog barks” - Be the calm, wise lion ignoring a noisy pup."
msgstr "- \"Die leeu draai nie om wanneer 'n klein hondjie blaf nie\" - Maak of jy 'n kalm, wyse leeu is wat 'n rasende hondjie ignoreer."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "- “Wisdom is like a baobab tree - no one can embrace it alone” - Stand in a circle and stretch your arms to build a tree together."
msgstr "- \"Wysheid is soos 'n kremetartboom - niemand kan dit alleen omhels nie\" - Staan in 'n sirkel en strek jou arms om 'n boom te vorm."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "- “A single bracelet does not jingle” - Clap or tap together and see how much louder it is with more hands!"
msgstr "- \"Een armband maak nie 'n geluid nie\" - Klap of tik en kyk hoeveel harder dit kan wees met meer hande!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This playful activity helps children explore big ideas like courage, kindness, and teamwork - through their bodies and imagination 💡"
msgstr "Hierdie prettige aktiwiteit help kinders om groot idees te verken, soos moed, vriendelikheid en spanwerk - deur hulle liggaampies en verbeelding 💡"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*I'm a Writer!*"
msgstr "*Ek's 'n Skrywer!*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📝 Have fun being creative with writing!"
msgstr "📝 Geniet dit om kreatief te wees met skryfwerk!"

#. type=text
#. Strings like @fields.xxx and @results.yyy should not be translated. 
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You and @fields.child_nickname can have fun writing with a pencil and paper, or with a stick and the sand!"
msgstr "Jy en @fields.child_nickname kan skryfpret hê met 'n potlood op papier, of met 'n stokkie in die sand!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "If your child doesn’t know how to write letters, encourage them to draw shapes, and try to copy the shapes of letters. 🔵▶️"
msgstr "As kinders nie weet hoe om letters te skryf nie, moedig hulle aan om vorms te teken en te probeer om die vorms van letters na te boots.🔵▶️"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "When they are more confident, encourage them to write letters and even words. 😃"
msgstr "Wanneer hulle meer selfvertroue het, moedig hulle aan om meer letters en woorde te skryf. 😃"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Start showing them how to write their name and other important words for them, like mom, ball or milk."
msgstr "Begin deur vir hulle te wys hoe om hulle naam en ander belangrike woorde te skryf, soos ma, bal of melk."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Show them the simple things that you write - like shopping lists! Show them the words and each of the letters. Let them try to copy the words! 📖"
msgstr "Wys vir hulle die eenvoudige goed wat jy skryf - soos inkopielysies! Wys vir hulle die woorde en elke letter. Laat hulle probeer om die woorde te kopieer! 📖"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You and your child can have fun writing with a pencil and paper, or with a stick and the sand!"
msgstr "Jy en jou kind kan skryfpret hê met 'n potlood op papier, of met 'n stokkie in die sand!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎉This playful writing time builds confidence, creativity, and early literacy - helping your child see that writing is useful and fun."
msgstr "🎉 Hierdie prettige skryftyd bou selfvertroue, kreatiwiteit en vroeë geletterdheid - dit help jou kind om te sien dat skryf nuttig en lekker is."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*A Friendly Chat*"
msgstr "*'n Vriendelike geselsie*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Talk to your child about something that they are interested in! 😃"
msgstr "Praat met jou kind oor wat vir hom/haar interessant is! 😃"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💚 Spending quality time with your child and talking to them every day is a good way to develop a strong relationship. "
msgstr "💚 Om kwaliteittyd met jou kind te spandeer en daagliks met hom/haar te gesels, is 'n goeie manier om 'n sterk verhouding te ontwikkel. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⚽ An easy way to start talking to your child is to ask them about something they are interested in, for example you could talk about topics such as: sports, books, movies, friends, music, celebrities, or school."
msgstr "⚽ 'n Maklike manier om met jou kind te begin gesels, is om uit te vra oor iets wat hom/haar interesseer. Jy kan byvoorbeeld oor onderwerpe praat soos sport, boeke, flieks, vriende, musiek, bekendes of skool."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂 You may not find everything your child shares to be interesting, but it’s important to show enthusiasm and an eagerness to learn."
msgstr "👂 Nie alles wat jou kind met jou deel, gaan vir jou interessant wees nie, maar dis belangrik om entoesiasme te wys, asook gretigheid om meer uit te vind."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Talking about their interests builds trust, confidence, and communication skills - and shows your child that what they care about matters to you 💛"
msgstr "Om oor hul belangstelling te praat, bou vertroue en kommunikasievaardighede - dit wys jou kind dat hulle belangstelling is vir jou belangrik💛"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Get Active*"
msgstr "*Raak aktief*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Exercise is a great way to spend time together and it is so good for your health. "
msgstr "Oefening is 'n goeie manier om tyd saam te spandeer en dis goed vir jou gesondheid."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🌱 Find a sport or exercise that both you and your child want to do and try it out together! "
msgstr "🌱 Vind 'n sport of oefening wat beide jy en jou kind sal geniet en probeer dit saam!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⏰ Even walking for 10 minutes a day is good for you. "
msgstr "⏰ Selfs 10 minute se stap per dag is goed vir jou. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⚽ Together you can walk, run, play soccer, swim, dance, or do any other sport."
msgstr "⚽ Julle kan saam hardloop, sokker speel, swem, dans of enige ander sport doen."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🏆 Together, think of ways to make it even more fun. Can you jog to a certain point? Take turns being the coach? Can there be a small, free reward, like getting to decide the next activity?"
msgstr "🏆 Dink saam aan maniere om dit selfs nog meer pret te maak. Kan julle tot by 'n sekere plek draf? Beurte neem om die afrigter te wees? Kan daar 'n klein, gratis beloning wees, soos om die volgende aktiwiteit te mag kies?"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🌈 Exercise becomes easier and more enjoyable the more you do it. "
msgstr "🌈 Oefening raak makliker en meer genotvol, hoe meer jy dit doen. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 If you or your child do not like the first exercise you pick, try a new exercise."
msgstr "🔄 As jy en jou kind nie van die eerste oefening wat julle gekies het, hou nie, probeer 'n nuwe een."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Pass the Ball*"
msgstr "*Gee die Bal aan*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Games are a great, fun way to spend time with your family! "
msgstr "Speletjies is 'n wonderlike, prettige manier om tyd saam met jou gesin deur te bring! "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "3️⃣ This game is best with at least 3 people."
msgstr "3️⃣Hierdie speletjie werk die beste met ten minste 3 mense."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⚽ Find a ball to play. If you cannot find a ball, choose an item you can safely throw around. For example, a bottle cap or a plastic cup."
msgstr "⚽ Kry 'n bal om mee te speel. As julle nie 'n bal kan kry nie, kies 'n item wat julle veilig kan rondgooi, byvoorbeeld 'n bottelprop of 'n plastiekglasie."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "➡️ Start in a circle and pass the ball around."
msgstr "➡️ Begin in 'n sirkel en gooi die bal in die rondte."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 Start throwing the ball in new directions (up, down, straight, curved, rolling on the ground) and with different forces (hard, soft, medium). You can bounce the ball, throw it in the air, and catch it a few times before passing it. "
msgstr "👋 Begin die bal in nuwe rigtings gooi (op, af, reguit, met 'n kurwe, rol dit op die grond) en met wisselende krag (hard, sag, medium). Jy kan die bal bons, dit in die lug gooi en dit 'n paar keer in die lug gooi en vang voordat jy dit aanstuur. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "✨ When everyone gets good at catching the ball, you can start moving around the room, still passing the ball. "
msgstr "✨ Wanneer almal begin goed raak daarmee om die bal te vang, kan julle begin om in die vertrek rond te beweeg en steeds vir mekaar die bal aan te gee. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⭐ Can you throw the ball under the leg? Behind the back? Over your head? Block a pass? Have fun with it!"
msgstr "⭐ Kan jy die bal tussen jou bene deur gooi? Agter jou rug? Oor jou kop? 'n Aangee blokkeer? Geniet dit!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Follow the Leader!*"
msgstr "*Volg die Leier!*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⭐ Choose someone to be the leader (tip: start with an adult like yourself)."
msgstr "⭐ Kies iemand om die leier te wees (wenk: begin met 'n volwassene soos jyself)."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "😃 Other players line up behind the leader. The leader moves around in any way they like!"
msgstr "😃 Ander spelers maak 'n ry agter die leier. Die leier beweeg rond op enige manier wat hulle wil!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🏁 They can run, jump, crawl, walk on tiptoe, and any other way they want!"
msgstr "🏁 Hulle kan hardloop, spring, kruip, op hulle tone loop, en enige ander manier wat hulle wil!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 The other players must copy what the leader does, and the leader can change movements at any time."
msgstr "👀 Die ander spelers moet die leier se bewegings naboots, en die leier kan te eniger tyd die bewegings verander."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Take turns being the leader, and remember, you can play with just two people or as many as you want!"
msgstr "🔄 Maak beurte om die leier te wees en onthou dat jy met net twee mense kan speel, of meer as jy wil!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This game builds movement skills, attention and listening, and self-control, while having fun together! 👂 "
msgstr "Hierdie speletjie bou bewegingsvaardighede, aandag, luister en selfbeheersing, terwyl julle pret saam het! 👂 "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Emotion Cards*"
msgstr "*Emosiekaarte*"

#. type=text
#. Strings like @fields.xxx and @results.yyy should not be translated. 
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Create cards of the main six emotions with @fields.child_nickname: happy, sad, angry, disgusted, surprised, afraid 😃😔😣"
msgstr "Ontwerp saam met @fields.child_nickname kaarte met die ses belangrikste emosies: gelukkig, hartseer, kwaad, gewalg, verras, bang 😃😔😣"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔶 Draw, cut-out pictures from magazines, or take photos of family members showing different emotions. "
msgstr "🔶 Teken, knip prente uit 'n tydskrif, of neem foto's van gesinslede wat verskillende emosies toon. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📝 Label each emotion and describe how each family member feels those emotions."
msgstr "📝 Etiketteer elke emosie en beskryf hoe elke familielid daardie emosie voel."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Create cards of the main six emotions with your child: happy, sad, angry, disgusted, surprised, afraid 😃😔😣"
msgstr "Ontwerp saam met jou kind kaarte met die ses belangrikste emosies daarop: gelukkig, hartseer, kwaad, gewalg, verras, bang 😃😔😣"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🚩 Put the cards in a spot everyone agrees on, and use it throughout the day to name how everyone is feeling. For example, after school, everyone can point out the emotion they are experiencing. "
msgstr "🚩 Plaas die kaarte op 'n plek waaroor almal saamstem en gebruik dit deur die dag om te sê hoe elkeen voel. Na skool kan almal byvoorbeeld die emosies uitwys wat hulle ervaar."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 Feel free to add new feelings as they come up. If someone doesn’t know what they are feeling, help them identify it by exploring how it feels in their body. Try together to find a new word for that emotion."
msgstr "💡 Voeg gerus meer emosies by soos dit voorkom. As iemand nie weet wat hulle voel nie, help hulle om dit te identifiseer deur dit in hul liggaam te verken. Probeer om saam 'n nuwe woord vir die emosie te vind."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This can help everyone in the family become experts in understanding themselves and be aware of what their bodies need! 💛"
msgstr "Dit kan almal in die gesin help om kenners te word en hulself te verstaan en om bewus te raak van wat hul liggaam nodig het! 💛"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*What's New?*"
msgstr "*Wat’s Nuut?*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Learning together is fun! 🎓"
msgstr "Om saam te leer, is pret! 🎓"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "❓ Ask your child to think of a new, fun skill you could learn together. "
msgstr "❓ Vra jou kind om te dink aan 'n nuwe, prettige vaardigheid wat julle saam kan leer. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "For example: keeping a ball in the air with your foot, juggling, making soup, moonwalking, whistling, saying the alphabet backwards, learning all the countries in Africa. "
msgstr "Byvoorbeeld: om 'n bal met jou voet in die lug te hou, \"juggle\", sop maak, \"moonwalk\", fluit, die alfabet agterstevoor op te sê, al die lande in Afrika te leer. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Take turns trying out the new skill. Make sure to praise each other and learn and play together!"
msgstr "🔄 Neem beurte om die nuwe vaardigheid te probeer. Maak seker dat julle mekaar prys, leer en saam speel!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💛 Approach learning the skill in a kind and fun way, and do not judge your child or yourself for your ability in the skill. "
msgstr "💛 Benader die leer van 'n vaardigheid op 'n vriendelike, prettige manier en moenie jou kind of jouself oordeel oor jul vermoë in die vaardigheid nie. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "😃 Once you have mastered the skill, choose another skill to learn together."
msgstr "😃 As julle die vaardigheid bemeester het, kies 'n ander vaardigheid om saam aan te leer."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Five Stones*"
msgstr "*Vyf Klippies*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let’s test your speed and skill with this classic hand game played across South Africa! ⭐"
msgstr "Kom ons toets jou spoed en vaardighede met hierdie klassieke handspeletjie, wat regoor Suid-Afrika gespeel word! ⭐"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "5️⃣ You’ll need five small stones (or any small objects you have around)."
msgstr "5️⃣ Jy het vyf klein klippies nodig (of klein voorwerpe wat jy beskikbaar het)."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "▶️ Start by placing all five on the ground. Pick up one and throw it gently into the air. While it’s in the air, quickly grab one stone from the ground and catch the first stone before it lands."
msgstr "▶️ Begin deur al vyf op die grond te sit. Tel een op en gooi dit versigtig in die lug. Terwyl dit in die lug is, gryp vinnig een klippie van die grond af en vang die eerste klippie voor dit val."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Repeat this, picking up one stone at a time. Then try two at once, then three... all the way to four!"
msgstr "🔄 Herhaal dit, soos jy elke keer een klippie op 'n slag optel. Probeer dan twee op 'n slag ... tot by vier!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🚩 Play alone or with friends, and see who can complete the challenge without dropping a stone!"
msgstr "🚩 Speel alleen of saam met vriende en kyk wie kan die uitdaging voltooi sonder om die klip te laat val!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This traditional game builds hand-eye coordination, focus, and timing - and it’s lots of fun to master ✅"
msgstr "Hierdie tradisionele speletjie bou hand-oog-koördinasie, fokus en tydsberekening - en dis tonne pret om dit te bemeester ✅"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Clap & Sing Game*"
msgstr "*Klap-en-Singspeletjie*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎵 Sit face-to-face with your child and try a fun clapping rhyme together. "
msgstr "🎵 Sit aangesig-tot-aangesig met jou kind en probeer 'n prettige handeklapritme saam. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 Clap your hands, then each other’s, and repeat with a rhythm and song from your childhood – or make up a new one."
msgstr "👋 Klap julle hande, dan mekaar s'n, en herhaal met 'n ritme en liedjie van jou kinderjare - of maak 'n nuwe een op."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💚 Follow the words with a simple clapping pattern. You can swap in your own words or names to make it even more fun!"
msgstr "💚 Volg die woorde met 'n eenvoudige handeklappatroon. Jy kan jou eie woorde of name gebruik om dit meer pret te maak!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "These clapping games have been popular among children from generation to generation, and help build rhythm, timing, memory, and laughter ✨"
msgstr "Hierdie handeklapspeletjies is reeds geslagte lank baie gewild onder kinders, en dit help om ritme, tydsberekening, geheue en lag te ontwikkel ✨"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Skipping Rope Song*"
msgstr "* Springtouliedjie*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎈 Find a long rope or make one from tied-up tights or string. "
msgstr "🎈 Soek 'n lang tou of maak een van sykouse of stringe wat aan mekaar gebind is. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "2️⃣ Two people turn the rope while one jumps in the middle. "
msgstr "2️⃣ Twee mense swaai die tou, terwyl een in die middel spring."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎵 Sing a song together as they jump – do you remember one from your childhood or can you use a different song you all know? "
msgstr "🎵 Sing 'n liedjie saam terwyl hulle spring - onthou jy een uit jou kinderjare of kan julle 'n ander liedjie sing wat almal ken? "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🏆 You can add fun moves like hopping, clapping, or even dancing while skipping. "
msgstr "🏆 Julle kan prettige bewegings byvoeg, soos hop, hande klap, of selfs dans terwyl julle spring. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💛 Then switch places so everyone gets a turn."
msgstr "💛 Ruil dan plekke om sodat elkeen 'n beurt kry."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This energetic game builds coordination, confidence, and teamwork - and brings a joyful beat to any outdoor play session 🌈"
msgstr "Hierdie energieke speletjies bou koördinasie, selfvertroue en spanwerk - en skep 'n vreugdevolle atmosfeer vir 'n buitespeelsessie 🌈"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Three Tin Tower*"
msgstr "*Driebliktoring*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔶 Stack three empty tins into a tower. "
msgstr "🔶 Pak drie leë blikkies op mekaar soos 'n toring."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔵 One player throws a soft ball to knock them down while others run away. "
msgstr "🔵 Een speler gooi 'n sagte bal om die blikkies om te gooi, terwyl die ander weghardloop."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⏰ The “tin guard” collects and rebuilds the tower as quickly as possible while trying to tag the runners."
msgstr "⏰ Die \"blikbeskermer\" versamel die blikke en herbou die bliktoring so vinnig as moontlik, terwyl hy poog om die hardlopers aan te raak."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 If you get tagged, you switch roles!"
msgstr "🔄 Wanneer jy geraak word, ruil julle rolle om!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This game is lots of fun and builds teamwork, movement skills, and fast thinking 🎉"
msgstr "Hierdie speletjie is propvol pret en bou spanwerk, bewegingsvaardighede en vinnige denke 🎉"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Story Stones*"
msgstr "*Storieklippies*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔴 Sit quietly with a handful of small stones. "
msgstr "🔴 Sit doodstil met 'n handvol klein klippies. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📖 Let your child imagine what the stones are, move them around and tell a story in their own words. It might be about animals, people, dreams, or anything they imagine."
msgstr "📖 Laat jou kind toe om hom/haar te verbeel dat die klippies iets anders is, laat hom/haar dit rondbeweeg en 'n storie in sy/haar eie woorde vertel. Dit kan gaan oor diere, mense, drome of enigiets waaraan hy/sy kan dink."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂You can listen quietly or help shape the story together."
msgstr "👂 Jy kan stil sit en luister of help om die storie vorm te gee."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This solo storytelling tradition helps children express feelings, practise language, and explore imagination - all through play and pretend 💛"
msgstr "Hierdie solo-storieverteltradisie help kinders om hul gevoelens te deel, taal te oefen en verbeelding te verken - alles deur speel en voorgee 💛"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "It’s a beautiful, calming game rooted in traditional storytelling 🌙"
msgstr "Dis 'n wonderlike kalmerende speletjie, gewortel in tradisionele storievertelling 🌙"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Hopscotch Fun*"
msgstr "*Eenbeentjie-pret*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let’s jump into a classic game! ☀️"
msgstr "Kom ons skop af met 'n klassieke speletjie! ☀️"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔷 Draw a hopscotch grid on the ground using chalk, a stick in the sand, or even tape on the floor indoors. Number the squares from 1 to 9."
msgstr "🔷 Teken 'n eenbeentjiediagram op die grond met kryt, stok in die grond, of selfs kleeflint op die vloer binne in die huis. Nommer die vierkantblokke van 1 tot 9."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔴 Give your child a small object (like a stone or bottle top) to toss into square 1. "
msgstr "🔴 Gee jou kind 'n klein voorwerpie (soos 'n klippie of 'n botteldoppie) om in vierkant 1 te gooi. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⬆️ Then they hop through the squares on one foot—skipping the square with the marker—then turn around and come back. "
msgstr "⬆️ Dan spring hy/sy op een been deur die vierkante - hy/sy mis die vierkant met die merker - en draai dan om en kom terug. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⬇️ Stop to pick up the marker on the way back, still hopping!"
msgstr "⬇️ Wanneer hy/sy terugkom, stop hy/sy om die merker op te tel, al springende!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Next round: throw the marker into square 2... and so on."
msgstr "🔄 Volgende rondte: gooi die merker in vierkant 2 ... en gaan so voort."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Hopscotch builds balance, counting, turn-taking, and fun movement skills. You can sing as you hop or make your own rules for extra challenge! 🎈"
msgstr "Eenbeentjie bou balans, tel, beurte maak en prettige bewegingsvaardighede. Jy kan sing terwyl jy spring, of maak jou eie reëls vir 'n ekstra uitdaging! 🎈"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Pattern Discovery*"
msgstr "*Patroon-ontdekking*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Did you know that patterns are all around us? 🎨"
msgstr "Het jy geweet dat patrone oral om ons is? 🎨"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🌷 Explore patterns together - whether it's the rows of palm trees outside or the design on their clothes. "
msgstr "🌷 Verken patrone saam - of dit die ry palmbome buite is of die ontwerp op hul klere. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔷 Line up colourful blocks, rocks, or feathers, or draw a pattern using simple shapes. Ask your child questions like: “What comes next?’” or “Can you create your own pattern?” "
msgstr "🔷 Sit kleurvolle blokke, klippe of vere neer, of teken 'n patroon deur eenvoudige vorms te gebruik. Vra jou kind vrae soos: \"Wat kom volgende?\" of \"Kan jy jou eie patroon maak?\" "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎉Remember to encourage and celebrate their curiosity as they explore the world of patterns!"
msgstr "🎉 Onthou om hom/haar aan te moedig en sy/haar nuuskierigheid te vier terwyl hy/sy die wêreld van patrone rondom hom/haar verken!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Your child will start by noticing patterns, and before you know it, they will be copying and creating their own patterns! 📝"
msgstr "Jou kind sal patrone begin oplet en voor jy weet, boots hy/sy patrone na of maak sy/haar eie! 📝"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Recognizing patterns helps prepare your child for future maths skills 💡"
msgstr "Patroonherkenning berei jou kind voor vir toekomstige wiskundige vaardighede 💡"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Guess the Emotion*"
msgstr "*Raai die Emosie*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Ask your child, “What does it look like when we’re happy? Angry? Surprised?” "
msgstr "👀 Vra jou kind: \"Hoe lyk dit wanneer ons gelukkig is? Kwaad? Verras?\" "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂 Take turns acting out different emotions and guessing what the other person is feeling. Using a silly voice, you can explain different reasons why you are feeling that emotion."
msgstr "👂 Maak beurte om verskillende emosies te wys en raai wat die ander persoon voel. Deur 'n snaakse stem te gebruik, kan jy verskillende redes gee waarom jy daardie emosie voel."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This isn’t just a game - it’s a chance for your child to learn how to recognize emotions in others 💚"
msgstr "Dit is nie net 'n speletjie nie - dis 'n geleentheid vir jou kind om te leer om emosies in ander te herken 💚"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "So, get ready to act out some emotions and "
msgstr "So, maak gereed om 'n paar emosies uit te beeld en "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "enjoy this special play activity together! 🌈"
msgstr "geniet hierdie spesiale speelaktiwiteit saam! 🌈"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Picture Puzzle*"
msgstr "*Prentelegkaart*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Get ready to turn a picture into a fun jigsaw puzzle that boosts memory and direction skills! 🎨"
msgstr "Maak gereed om 'n prent in 'n prettige legkaart te omskep om daardie geheue en aanwysingsvaardighede 'n hupstoot te gee 🎨"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📝 You’ll need scissors and a picture from a paper or magazine - or a picture that you have drawn yourself."
msgstr "📝Jy het 'n skêr en 'n prent uit 'n tydskrif of koerant nodig - of 'n prent wat julle self geteken het."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 First, cut the picture into at least three pieces. Older children can try cutting up the pieces for younger children if they already know how to use scissors safely."
msgstr "💡 Eerstens, knip die prent in ten minste drie stukke. Ouer kinders kan probeer om die dele op te knip vir jonger kinders, as hulle reeds weet hoe om 'n skêr te gebruik."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔷 Now, flip the pieces face down so you can’t see the picture."
msgstr "🔷 Draai nou die stukke met die gesigkant na onder, sodat jy nie die prent kan sien nie."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "✅ Your challenge? Rebuild the picture together by turning over one piece at a time and putting it back together."
msgstr "✅ Julle uitdaging? Herbou die prentjie saam deur een vir een die stukke om te draai en die prent weer aanmekaar te sit."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 If your child needs a little help, ask guiding questions like, 'Where do you think this piece goes?'"
msgstr "👀 As jou kind hulp nodig het, vra leidende vrae soos, \"Waar dink jy kom hierdie stuk?\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "It’s a quick and fun way to strengthen memory and problem-solving skills! ✨"
msgstr "Dis 'n vinnige en lekker manier om die kind se geheue en probleemoplossingsvaardighede te versterk! ✨"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/photo-puzzle"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/photo-puzzle"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Superhero Costume Raffle*"
msgstr "*Superheldkostuum-Lootjie*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You can transform into superheroes with this fun and imaginative dressing-up game! 👑"
msgstr "Jy kan in 'n superheld verander in hierdie prettige en verbeeldingryke aantrekspeletjie! 👑"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "2️⃣ Here’s what you’ll need: Two items of clothing for each person playing, and a pillowcase or bag to hold them."
msgstr "2️⃣Hier is wat jy nodig het: Twee kledingstukke vir elke persoon wat speel, en 'n kussingsloop of sak om alles in te sit."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎁 Start by placing all the clothes in the pillowcase. "
msgstr "🎁 Begin deur al die klere in die kussingsloop te sit. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Hand the pillowcase to the smallest player first. Make sure their eyes are shut, then let them pull out one item of clothing. "
msgstr "👀 Gee die kussingsloop eerste vir die kleinste speler. Maak seker dat sy/haar oë toe is, en laat hy/sy dan een kledingstuk uithaal. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Next, pass the case around until everyone gets two items of clothing. "
msgstr "🔄 Stuur dan die sloop in die rondte tot elkeen twee kledingstukke het. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "✨ Now, everyone takes turns to imagine what superpower their pieces of clothing give them. Maybe a scarf makes you fly, or a hat gives you super speed - it’s totally up to your imagination!"
msgstr "✨ Nou kry almal 'n geleentheid om hulle te verbeel watter superheld hulle gaan wees. Miskien laat die serp jou vlieg, of 'n hoed gee jou vinniger spoed - dit hang heeltemal van jou verbeelding af!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🚗 Now it’s time to play! Put on your superpower clothes and act out a story together, like saving the world from a monster."
msgstr "🚗 Nou is dit tyd om te speel! Trek jou superkragklere aan en speel saam 'n rollespel-storie, soos om die wêreld van 'n monster te red."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "It’s a fantastic way to encourage creative thinking, flexible language skills, and playful bonding 💛"
msgstr "Dis 'n fantastiese manier om kreatiewe denke, buigsame taalgebruik en prettige verbintenisse aan te moedig 💛"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/superhero-costume-lottery"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/superhero-costume-lottery"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Letter Hunt*"
msgstr "*Letterjag*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Turn your home into a scavenger hunt with this fun and interactive letter game ✅"
msgstr "Omskep jou huis in 'n skattejagterrein met hierdie prettige interaktiewe letterspeletjie ✅"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📝 Here is what you need: paper and a pen."
msgstr "📝 Hier is wat jy nodig het: papier en 'n pen."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "1️⃣ Start by writing down each letter of the alphabet - one letter per piece of paper. Once you are done, place the papers face down so you can’t see the letters."
msgstr "1️⃣ Begin deur elke letter van die alfabet neer te skryf - een letter per vel papier. Wanneer jy klaar is, plaas die papiere op hul gesigkant neer sodat jy nie die letters kan sien nie."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Now, turn over one piece of paper to reveal a letter. The challenge? Find objects around your house that begin with that letter! Once you've found an item, place it next to the letter on the paper."
msgstr "👀 Draai nou een papier om en wys die letter. Die uitdaging? Vind voorwerpe in en om jou huis wat met daardie letter begin! Sodra jy 'n item gevind het, sit dit langs die letter op die papier."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Keep the hunt going! Flip over the next letter and search for another object. Continue until you’ve gone through all the letters."
msgstr "🔄 Hou die skattejag aan die gang! Draai die volgende letter om en soek 'n ander voorwerp. Gaan voort tot jy deur al die letters gegaan het."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This activity is perfect for blending learning with active play, while giving your little ones a fun way to practise their alphabet and creativity! 💡"
msgstr "Hierdie aktiwiteit is perfek om leer met aktiewe spel te meng, terwyl jy jou kleinding 'n prettige manier wys om die alfabet en hul kreatiwiteit te oefen! 💡"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/what-we-see"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/what-we-see"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Hot or cold*"
msgstr "*Warm of Koud*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Ready to hunt for hidden treasure using clues? 🎁"
msgstr "Gereed om vir versteekte skatte te jag deur leidrade te gebruik? 🎁"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⚽ Here’s what you’ll need: something easy to hide, like toys or balls. "
msgstr "⚽ Hier is wat jy nodig het: iets wat jy maklik kan wegsteek, soos speelgoed of balle. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 One player hides an object, while the others close their eyes. The player who hid the object will now give clues to help the others find it. "
msgstr "👀 Een speler versteek 'n voorwerp, terwyl die ander hul oë toemaak. Die speler wat die voorwerp weggesteek het, sal leidrade gee om die ander te help om die voorwerp te kry. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "☀️ When the person searching is getting close to where the object is hidden, the hider can say “getting warm!” or “hot!”, and when the searcher is going in the wrong direction, the hider can say “getting colder…”."
msgstr "☀️ Wanneer die een wat soek, naby die versteekte voorwerp is, kan die versteker sê \"jy word warmer\" of \"warm\" en as die soeker in die verkeerde rigting gaan, kan die versteker sê \"jy word koud\"."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Take turns hiding objects and giving clues - it’s fun for everyone to get involved!"
msgstr "🔄 Maak beurte om die voorwerp weg te steek en leidrade te gee - dis pret vir almal om betrokke te raak!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 For an extra challenge, hide multiple objects around the house and create a treasure map."
msgstr "💡 Vir 'n ekstra uitdaging, steek meer voorwerpe rondom jou huis weg en maak 'n skatkaart."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This fun-filled game is perfect for challenging problem-solving and communication skills while keeping everyone engaged with exciting clues! ✨"
msgstr "Hierdie prettige speletjie is perfek vir uitdagende probleemoplossing en kommunikasievaardighede, terwyl almal betrokke gehou word met opwindende leidrade! ✨"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/treasure-hunt"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/treasure-hunt"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Shine a Light*"
msgstr "*Skyn 'n Lig*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Let your child choose an object that they would like to draw - it could be anything from around the house, like a cup or a favourite toy. \r\r📝 Have them place the object upright on a blank sheet of paper."
msgstr "👀 Laat jou kind 'n voorwerp kies wat hy/sy graag wil teken - dit kan enigiets in en om die huis wees, soos 'n koppie of 'n gunstelingspeelding. \r\r📝Laat jou kind die voorwerp regop op die leë vel papier neersit."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 Hold the light behind the object so the shadow appears on the paper. You can take turns holding the light, or rest it on something sturdy to keep your hands free for drawing."
msgstr "💡 Hou die lig agter die voorwerp sodat die skaduwee op die papier verskyn. Julle kan beurte maak om die lig vas te hou, of dit op iets stewigs laat rus om julle hande vry te hou om te teken."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎨 Now, guide your child so they can trace the shadow’s outline on the paper. "
msgstr "🎨 Help nou jou kind om die buitelyn van die skadu op die papier af te teken. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "✨ Once they have finished drawing the shape, it’s time to get creative! Colour and decorate the shadow together to add your own artistic touch."
msgstr "✨ Wanneer hy/sy klaar die vorm geteken het, is dit tyd om kreatief te raak! Versier en kleur die skadu saam in om julle eie kunstige gevoel te gee."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📖 For extra fun, make up a story about the shadow object together as you decorate. What is it doing today?"
msgstr "📖 Vir ekstra pret, maak saam 'n storie op oor die skaduvoorwerp terwyl julle dit versier. Wat sal dit vandag doen?"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This activity is a fun and imaginative way to boost creativity and flexible thinking while exploring shadows and light 🌈"
msgstr "Hierdie aktiwiteit is pret en verbeeldingryk, dit gee sy/haar kreatiwiteit en buigsame denke 'n hupstoot terwyl hy/sy die lig en skaduwees verken 🌈"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/shine-a-light"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/shine-a-light"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Colour Hunt*"
msgstr "*Kleurejag*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Get ready for a colourful adventure that will challenge your child’s thinking and focus 🎨"
msgstr "Maak gereed vir 'n kleurvolle avontuur wat uitdagend vir jou kinders se denke en fokus sal wees🎨"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "5️⃣ Gather 5 small objects with different colours (like crayons, building blocks or anything else you have in the house)."
msgstr "5️⃣ Maak 5 klein voorwerpe met verskillende kleure bymekaar (soos kryte, boublokkies of enigiets anders wat jy in die huis het)."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎁 Place all the coloured objects in a bag. Each participant picks one object from the bag to get started."
msgstr "🎁 Plaas al die gekleurde voorwerpe in 'n sak. Elke deelnemer kies een voorwerp uit die sak om te begin."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Now, the challenge begins! Each player must find three other objects around the house that are the same colour as the object they picked. Search everywhere for the perfect matches!"
msgstr "👀 Nou begin die uitdaging! Elke speler moet drie ander voorwerpe in en om die huis vind wat dieselfde kleur is as die voorwerp wat hy/sy gekies het. Soek oral vir die perfekte maat!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🚩 When a player finds an object that matches the colour, they place it next to the object and shout \"match!\""
msgstr "🚩 Wanneer 'n speler 'n voorwerp van dieselfde kleur vind, sit hy/sy dit langs die voorwerp neer en skree \"pas!\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Once a player has found three matching objects, they can head back to the bag, choose another colour, and start the hunt all over again!"
msgstr "🔄Wanneer 'n speler drie bypassende voorwerpe gevind het, kan hy/sy teruggaan na die sak om 'n ander kleur te kies en die skattejag weer van vooraf begin!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Colour Hunt is a fantastic way to boost focus, encourage problem-solving, and keep everyone moving and engaged. Let the colourful treasure hunt begin! ✅"
msgstr "Kleurejag is 'n fantastiese manier om sy/haar fokus 'n hupstoot te gee, probleemoplossing aan te moedig en almal aan die beweeg en betrokke te hou. Laat die kleurvolle skattejag begin!✅"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/colour-hunt"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/colour-hunt"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Round & Round*"
msgstr "*Al In Die Rondte*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 Grab each other’s hands and form a circle. "
msgstr "👋Vat mekaar se hande en maak 'n sirkel. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎵 Walk round and round while you sing a song you know – it could be one from your childhood like “Ring-a-Rosy” or “Sawa Sonke”, or a favourite your child loves. "
msgstr "🎵 Loop al in die rondte terwyl julle 'n liedjie sing wat julle ken - dit kan een uit jou kinderjare wees soos \"Wielie-Wielie-Walie\" of jou kind se gunsteling."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎉 As you go round, add some silly moves to make it even more fun. Try hopping on one leg, see if you can put your leg over the next person’s arm, or gently fall to the ground when the song finishes. "
msgstr "🎉 Terwyl julle in die rondte beweeg, voeg 'n paar lawwe bewegings by om dit selfs nog meer pret te maak. Probeer om op een been te spring, kyk of jy jou been oor die ander een se arm kan sit, of val saggies op die grond wanneer die liedjie klaar is. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Take turns choosing the next move or song!"
msgstr "🔄 Maak beurte om die volgende musiek of beweging te kies!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This activity builds connection, encourages coordination and balance, and sparks lots of laughter and creativity 😃"
msgstr "Hierdie aktiwiteit bou verbintenis, moedig koördinasie en balans aan en laat vrolikheid en kreatiwiteit opvlam 😃"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Freeze Like a Statue*"
msgstr "*Vries Soos 'n Standbeeld*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Let your child shape you into a frozen statue - you might be a tree, a happy, sad or angry person, or anything else they imagine!"
msgstr "👀 Laat jou kind jou soos 'n standbeeld toemaak - jy kan dalk 'n boom wees, 'n persoon wat gelukkig, hartseer of kwaad is, of enigiets waaraan hy/sy kan dink!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🚩 You can even invite others to join and let your child shape you all into a frozen scene, like a classroom, a soccer match, or something completely silly."
msgstr "🚩 Jy kan selfs ander saamnooi, dat jou kind almal in 'n gevriesde toneel vorm, soos 'n klaskamer, 'n sokkerwedstryd of iets heeltemal laf."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📱 Once the statue is ready, your child can be the ‘photographer’ and take a pretend (or real!) picture. "
msgstr "📱 Wanneer die standbeeld gereed is, kan jou kind die \"fotograaf\" wees en maak of hy/sy 'n foto neem (of 'n regte foto neem). "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Then swap roles and let them be the statue next."
msgstr "🔄 Ruil dan rolle om en laat hy/sy nou weer die standbeeld wees."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This activity encourages creativity, role-play, and imagination - while building confidence through leading and observing ⭐"
msgstr "Hierdie aktiwiteit moedig kreatiwiteit, rolspel en verbeelding aan - terwyl selfvertroue gebou word deur leiding en waarneming⭐"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Peg and Pretend*"
msgstr "*Pennetjies en Rolspel*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Get creative with easy household items! 🧸"
msgstr "Raak kreatief met huishoudelike items!🧸"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 Grab 10 clothing pegs – or more if you have – and build a shape by pegging them together. Let your child build their own creation too!"
msgstr "👋 Kry 10 wasgoedpennetjies - of meer as jy wil - en bou 'n figuur deur die pennetjies aan mekaar vas te knyp. Laat jou kind ook sy/haar eie skepping maak!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "\r🎨 Ask your child what their shape could be. A bug? A spaceship? A crocodile? Act out a little story using the peg creations."
msgstr "\r🎨 Vra jou kind wat sy/haar figuur kan wees. 'n Gogga? 'n Ruimteskip? 'n Krokodil? Rolspel 'n kort storie deur die pennetjieskeppings te gebruik."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "\r🔄 Then build something new and let the next story begin!"
msgstr "\r🔄 Bou dan iets anders en laat die volgende storie begin!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Did you know that these imagination games help your child develop thinking, creativity, fine motor skills, and hand-eye coordination? All from a few simple pegs and a lot of imagination! 💡 "
msgstr "Het jy geweet dat hierdie verbeeldingspeletjies jou kind se denkwyse, kreatiwiteit, fyn motoriese vaardighede en hand-oog-koördinasie ontwikkel? Alles met 'n paar eenvoudige pennetjies en baie verbeelding! 💡 "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "\rAdapted from UNICEF Playbox: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yYt2ziDgvRI"
msgstr "\rAangepas uit UNICEF Playbox: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yYt2ziDgvRI"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Wind Power*"
msgstr "*Windkrag*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let’s explore the magic of wind with a fun movement game! ✨"
msgstr "Kom ons verken die towerkrag van wind met 'n prettige bewegingspeletjie! ✨"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 First, talk with your child about the wind. Can you see it? Taste it? How does it feel on your hair or your skin?"
msgstr "👀 Gesels eerstens met jou kind oor die wind. Kan jy dit sien? Dit proe? Hoe voel dit op jou hare of jou vel?"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔶 Take a piece of card or a leaf, close your eyes, and blow it using your own wind power. Watch how it moves!"
msgstr "🔶 Neem 'n stukkie karton of 'n blaar, maak jou oë toe en blaas dit deur jou eie windkrag. Hou dop hoe dit beweeg!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔵 Now try heavier things. Can you blow a spoon or small stones? What’s different?"
msgstr "🔵 Probeer nou swaarder goed. Kan jy 'n lepel of klippies blaas? Wat is anders?"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎨 Time to play with water and wind! Drop small amounts of water on a plate or piece of plastic. Blow the water gently across the surface - you can make a straw to blow through by rolling up a small piece of paper."
msgstr "🎨 Tyd om met water en wind te speel! Drup klein bietjies water op 'n bord of 'n stuk plastiek. Blaas die water saggies oor die oppervlak - jy kan 'n strooitjie maak om deur te blaas deur 'n stukkie papier op te rol."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🏆 You can even place objects and try blowing the water around them to trace their shape."
msgstr "🏆 Jy kan selfs voorwerpe daarop plaas en die water rondom blaas om die vorm na te spoor."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This sensory activity helps your child understand movement, space, and airflow - while sparking creativity and laughter 💡 "
msgstr "Hierdie sensoriese aktiwiteit help om beweging, spasie en lugvloei te verstaan - terwyl kreatiwiteit en vrolikheid aangewakker word💡 "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "\rAdapted from UNICEF Playbox: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=COZu4eJltow"
msgstr "\rAangepas uit UNICEF Playbox: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=COZu4eJltow"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Blanket Forts*"
msgstr "*Kombersforte*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let’s dive into creating your very own cosy hideaway! 🧸"
msgstr "Kom ons begin om jou eie gesellige wegkruipplek te maak! 🧸"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 First, gather everything you’ll need - blankets, pillows, chairs, and maybe even a table. If you want to add a little magic, grab a light to light up your fort."
msgstr "👋 Eerstens, maak alles bymekaar wat jy gaan nodig hê - komberse, kussings en miskien ook 'n tafel. Indien jy 'n bietjie misterie wil byvoeg, kry 'n lig om jou fort te verlig."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔷 Now, it’s time to build. Start by setting up two chairs facing each other, or use a table as the main structure of your fort. "
msgstr "🔷 Nou is dit tyd om te bou. Begin deur twee stoele teenoor mekaar te sit, of gebruik die tafel as die hoofstruktuur van die fort. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 Drape the blankets over the chairs or table to create a roof. Don’t forget to secure them - use clothing pegs or something heavy to hold everything in place so your fort stays strong!"
msgstr "👋 Drapeer die komberse oor die stoele of tafel om 'n dak te vorm. Moenie vergeet om dit stewig vas te maak nie - gebruik wasgoedpennetjies of iets swaar om alles in plek te hou, sodat jou fort staande bly!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔴 Next, make the inside extra comfy with pillows or blankets. "
msgstr "🔴 Maak nou die binnekant ekstra gemaklik met kussings of komberse. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎈 Once your fort is built, add some fun touches. Ask your child to bring their favourite toys or books, and decorate the space however you like. "
msgstr "🎈 Sodra jou fort klaar is, voeg 'n paar prettige goed by. Vra jou kind om sy/haar gunstelingspeelgoed of boeke te bring en versier die spasie net soos jy wil. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📝 You could even make a “welcome” sign together to make it feel like your very own special house!"
msgstr "📝 Julle kan selfs saam 'n \"welkom\"-teken maak sodat dit soos jul eie spesiale huis voel!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🌙 Now, crawl inside and enjoy your new fort! This is your cosy, creative space for reading stories, playing games, or just spending some quiet time together."
msgstr "🌙 Kruip nou binne-in en geniet julle nuwe fort! Hierdie is jul gesellige, kreatiewe spasie vir stories lees, speletjies speel, of net om stiltetyd saam te spandeer."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Building a blanket fort is more than just a fun activity - it’s a chance to spark creativity, solve problems, and share special moments together. So, grab those blankets and start building your adventure today! 💡"
msgstr "Om 'n kombersfort te bou, is meer as net 'n prettige aktiwiteit - dis 'n geleentheid om kreatiwiteit aan te wakker, probleme op te los en spesiale oomblikke saam te deel. Gryp daardie komberse en begin bou aan jou avontuur!💡"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Tricky Tower*"
msgstr "*Stapeltoring*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Here is an exciting activity that will test your child’s ability to estimate risks, work as a team, and think creatively - all while having fun and developing fine motor skills ⭐ "
msgstr "Hier is 'n opwindende aktiwiteit wat jou kind se vermoë sal toets om risiko te evalueer, in 'n span te werk en kreatief te dink - alles terwyl hy/sy dit geniet en sy/haar fyn motoriese vaardighede ontwikkel word⭐ "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔶 Start by giving your child building blocks or something else they can stack. "
msgstr "🔶 Begin deur vir jou kind boublokkies te gee, of iets wat hy/sy op mekaar kan stapel. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 Ask them to build a tower by stacking the blocks, using just one hand. This challenge helps build focus and concentration as they balance the blocks carefully."
msgstr "👋 Vra hom/haar om 'n toring te bou deur net een hand te gebruik om blokkies op mekaar te stapel. Hierdie uitdaging help om fokus en konsentrasie te bevorder terwyl hy/sy die blokkies versigtig balanseer."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "\r⬆️ If other children or adults are around, you can make it into a match to see who can build the tallest tower the fastest."
msgstr "\r⬆️ As ander kinders en volwassenes teenwoordig is, kan julle dit 'n kompetisie maak om te kyk wie kan die hoogste toring die vinnigste bou."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Make the game even more challenging by asking your child to using their non-dominant hand. They’ll have to balance their wish to build the tallest tower with the risk of the tower collapsing."
msgstr "🔄 Maak die speletjie selfs meer uitdagend deur jou kind te vra om die nie-dominante hand te gebruik. Dit sal sy/haar wens om die hoogste toring te bou, balanseer met die risiko dat die toring in duie kan stort."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This isn’t just about building - it’s about problem-solving, persistence, and teamwork 💛"
msgstr "Dit gaan hier nie net oor bou nie - dit gaan oor probleemoplossing, volharding en spanwerk 💛"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Tricky Tower is a fantastic way to help your child develop important skills while having fun with friends or family 🏆"
msgstr "Die stapeltoring is 'n fantastiese manier om jou kind te help om belangrike vaardighede te ontwikkel terwyl hy/sy dit saam met vriende of familie geniet 🏆"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/tricky-tower"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/tricky-tower"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Flip the blanket*"
msgstr "*Draai die Kombers om*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Can you and your child flip a blanket while standing on it? 🚩"
msgstr "Kan jy en jou kind 'n kombers omdraai terwyl julle daarop staan? 🚩"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⬇️ Start by laying a blanket or large piece of cloth flat on the ground. Have all the players stand on the blanket - make sure no one steps off!"
msgstr "⬇️ Begin deur 'n kombers of 'n groot stuk lap op die grond te sit. Laat al die spelers op die kombers staan - maak seker dat niemand afklim nie!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 Now, the challenge begins. The players must work together to flip the blanket over without stepping off or touching the ground."
msgstr "👋 Nou begin die uitdaging. Al die spelers moet saamwerk om die kombers om te draai, sonder om af te klim of die grond te raak."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔑 Experiment with different ideas, try new strategies, and see what works best!"
msgstr "🔑 Eksperimenteer met verskillende idees, probeer nuwe strategieë en kyk wat die beste werk!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 If anyone touches the ground, no worries - just start over and give it another try."
msgstr "🔄 As enigiemand die grond raak, geen probleem - begin net oor en probeer weer."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 While you are playing, talk about the problem-solving you are doing. Ask the players what ideas they are trying and why, how they are working together, and what is working and what is not. Discuss how they came up with solutions as a team."
msgstr "👀 Terwyl julle speel, gesels oor die probleemoplossing wat julle nou doen. Vra die spelers watter idees hulle probeer en hoekom, hoe hulle saam werk, wat werk en wat werk nie. Bespreek hoe hulle as 'n span met die oplossing vorendag gekom het."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Flip the Blanket is a fantastic way to encourage teamwork, creative thinking, problem solving, and perseverance - all while having a great time together! 🎉"
msgstr "Draai-die-Kombers-om is 'n fantastiese manier om spanwerk, kreatiewe denkwyse, probleemoplossing en deursettingsvermoë aan te moedig - alles terwyl julle 'n wonderlike tyd saam het! 🎉"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/flip-the-blanket"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/flip-the-blanket"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Can You Catch It?*"
msgstr "*Kan Jy Dit Vang?*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let’s see if you can follow instructions while catching a ball! ⚽"
msgstr "Kom ons kyk of jou kind instruksies kan volg terwyl hy/sy 'n bal vang! ⚽"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "✅ Start by standing about three metres apart and gently throw a ball at each other. After a few easy throws, it’s time to introduce the rules!"
msgstr "✅ Begin deur so drie meter uitmekaar te staan en gooi die bal versigtig vir mekaar. Na 'n paar maklike gooie, is dit tyd om die reëls bekend te stel!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "1️⃣ When the thrower shouts ‘one’, the catcher has to catch the ball with their right hand and put their left foot out. "
msgstr "1️⃣ Wanneer die gooier 'een' skree, moet die vanger die bal met sy/haar regterhand vang en sy/haar linkervoet uitsit. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "2️⃣ If the thrower shouts ‘two’, the catcher catches with their left hand and puts their right foot out."
msgstr "2️⃣ As die gooier 'twee' skree, moet die vanger met die bal met sy/haar linkerhand vang en sy/haar regtervoet uitsit."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⭐ Once you’re confident, add some extra numbers and rules! "
msgstr "⭐ Sodra julle selfversekerd is, voeg 'n paar ekstra getalle by! "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⏰ For the game to work, make sure the number is called before you throw the ball, so the catcher has time to react!"
msgstr "⏰ Vir die speletjie om te werk, maak seker dat die getal geroep is voordat die bal gegooi word, sodat die vanger tyd het om te reageer!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🚩 You can adjust the rules to make it perfect for every age."
msgstr "🚩 Jy kan die reëls aanpas om dit perfek te maak vir enige ouderdom."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This activity is a great way to improve coordination, concentration, and quick thinking - all while having fun! So, grab a ball and start throwing with these new rules to test your skills! 💡 "
msgstr "Hierdie aktiwiteit is 'n goeie manier om koördinasie, konsentrasie en vinnige denke te verbeter - alles terwyl daar pret is! So, gryp 'n bal en begin gooi met die nuwe reëls om jou vaardighede te toets! 💡 "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/can-you-catch-it"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/can-you-catch-it"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Unseen Guesses*"
msgstr "*Ongesiene Raaiskote*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You can do this activity when you are together with at least three people in total 3️⃣"
msgstr "Jy kan hierdie aktiwiteit doen wanneer jy saam met ten minste drie mense in totaal is 3️⃣"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Ask your child and another child/adult to sit next to each other. Blindfold both using a scarf or hat. "
msgstr "👀 Vra jou kind en 'n ander kind/volwassene om langs mekaar te sit. Blinddoek beide met 'n serp of hoed. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🚗 Give your child an object and ask them to feel it and describe it, without saying the name of the object!"
msgstr "🚗 Gee jou kind 'n voorwerp en vra dat hy/sy daaraan voel en dit beskryf, sonder om die naam van die voorwerp te sê!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎁 The other person’s job is to figure out what the object is based on the description. "
msgstr "🎁 Die ander persoon moet raai wat die voorwerp is, gebaseer op die beskrywing. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "✅ The “guesser” can ask questions, but the “speaker” can only answer with \"yes\" or \"no\"."
msgstr "✅ Die \"raaier\" kan vrae vra, maar die \"spreker\" kan net \"ja\" of \"nee\" antwoord."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 After each round, swap roles and play again, giving everyone a chance to be the “speaker” and “guesser” and the one to provides the object."
msgstr "🔄 Na elke rondte, ruil rolle om en speel weer, gee elkeen kans om die \"spreker\", die \"raaier\" en die verskaffer van die voorwerpe te wees."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This game is not only fun but also helps children develop strong communication skills and teaches them how to work together to achieve a goal. Enjoy working through the challenge of Unseen Guesses! 💚"
msgstr "Hierdie speletjie is nie net pret nie, maar dit help kinders om sterk kommunikasievaardighede te ontwikkel, om saam te werk en om doelwitte te bereik. Geniet die uitdaging van Ongesiene Raaiskote! 💚"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/unseen-guesses"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/unseen-guesses"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Things that Make Me Happy*"
msgstr "*Dinge wat my Gelukkig maak*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let’s take some time to appreciate the little things that make us feel happy every day 😃"
msgstr "Laat ons die tyd neem om die klein goedjies wat ons elke dag gelukkig maak, te waardeer😃"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💛 Start by talking with your child about the things that made you happy today. It could be anything - a friend, a favourite pet, an activity that made you smile."
msgstr "💛 Begin deur met jou kind te gesels oor dinge wat jou vandag gelukkig gemaak het. Dit kan enigiets wees - 'n vriend, 'n gunstelingtroeteldier, 'n aktiwiteit wat jou laat glimlag het."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Next, find three things that represent what makes you happy and place them in a special container or box. "
msgstr "👀 Volgende, vind drie dinge wat die dinge wat jou gelukkig maak, verteenwoordig, en plaas dit in 'n spesiale houer of boks. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎨 If the things that make you happy are too big to fit in the box, or if you can’t find something to represent them, you can draw them!"
msgstr "🎨 As die goed wat jou gelukkig maak, te groot is om in die houer te pas, of as jy nie iets kan kry wat dit verteenwoordig nie, kan jy dit teken!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂 Once everything is in the box, discuss what you and your child chose. Ask them why these things make them happy. It’s a great way to get them talking about positive emotions."
msgstr "👂 Sodra alles in die houer is, bespreek wat jy en jou kind gekies het. Vra hom/haar hoekom hierdie goed hom/haar gelukkig maak. Dis 'n wonderlike manier om hom/haar oor positiewe emosies te laat praat."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You can play this game as often as you like - even daily! Doing this before bed can help your child stay motivated, happy, and calm, especially during tough times."
msgstr "Julle kan die speletjie so dikwels speel as wat julle wil - selfs daagliks! Om dit voor slaaptyd te doen, kan help dat jou kind meer gemotiveerd, gelukkig en kalm bly, veral deur rowwe tye."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "So, gather those happy things and create a special box full of joy! ⭐"
msgstr "So, versamel daardie gelukkige goed en maak 'n spesiale boks vol vreugde!⭐"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/things-that-make-me-happy"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/things-that-make-me-happy"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Nature Game*"
msgstr "*Natuurspeletjie*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let’s have some fun exploring the world around you with a nature-themed game! You can play it anywhere - at the beach, around your house, or even on a walk 🌷"
msgstr "Geniet dit om die wêreld rondom julle te verken deur 'n speletjie met 'n natuur-tema! Julle kan dit enige plek speel - by die see, rondom julle huis, of selfs op 'n uitstappie 🌷"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📝 First, draw a grid of 3 by 3 on a piece of paper and write something in each box that you might find in nature - like a tree, flower, rock, bird, or cloud."
msgstr "📝 Eerstens, teken 'n tabel van 3 by 3 op 'n stuk papier en skryf iets in elke blok wat jy dalk in die natuur kan vind - soos 'n boom, blom, klip, voël of wolk."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Now, it’s time to explore! Head outside and start searching for the items on your card. "
msgstr "👀 Nou is dit tyd om bietjie te verken! Gaan uit en begin soek vir die items op jou kaart. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "✅ Each time you find something, mark it off."
msgstr "✅ Elke keer as jy iets vind, merk dit af."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🏆 You decide when you win! Maybe it’s when you’ve marked off a whole line, or perhaps when you’ve found everything on your card. It’s completely up to you!"
msgstr "🏆 Jy besluit wanneer jy wen! Miskien is dit wanneer jy 'n hele ry afgemerk het, of dalk wanneer jy alles op die kaart gekry het. Dis geheel en al jou keuse!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Nature Game is a great way for your child to explore the outdoors, boost concentration, and have fun while learning more about the world around them. So, get outside and start your nature game! 🌱"
msgstr "Natuurspeletjie is 'n goeie manier vir jou kind om die buitelug te verken, sy/haar selfvertroue 'n hupstoot te gee en pret te hê terwyl hy/sy meer leer oor die wêreld om hom/haar. So, gaan uit en begin julle natuurspeletjie!🌱"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/nature-bingo"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/nature-bingo"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Baking Time*"
msgstr "*Baktyd*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Baking isn’t just about creating something delicious - it’s a fun and exciting way to learn new skills while exploring creativity 🍞 "
msgstr "Om te bak, is nie net om iets lekker te maak nie - dis 'n prettige en opwindende manier om nuwe vaardighede te leer, terwyl julle jul kreatiwiteit verken🍞 "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "From mixing to serving, your young chef will feel a sense of pride and accomplishment as they bring their tasty creations to life! ⭐"
msgstr "Vanaf meng tot bedien sal jou jong kok 'n gevoel van trots en prestasie voel terwyl hy/sy sy/haar smaaklike skeppings in die lewe roep!⭐"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📖 Here’s how to get started: Pick a simple recipe, like bread or cookies. "
msgstr "📖 Hoe om te begin: Kies 'n eenvoudige resep, soos brood of koekies. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👋 Let your child help with all the steps - mixing ingredients, whisking the batter, and stirring everything together. "
msgstr "👋 Laat jou kind met al die stappe help - meng bestanddele, klits die beslag en roer alles saam. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎨 If you are making bread or cookies, invite your child to make shapes with the dough. Don’t be afraid to get messy!"
msgstr "🎨 As julle brood of koekies maak, nooi jou kind om vorms met die deeg te maak. Moenie bang wees om vuil te word nie!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🚩 Once your treats are baking, the fun continues with cleaning up the mess! "
msgstr "🚩 Sodra julle lekkernye bak, gaan die pret voort wanneer julle die gemors opruim! "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "✅ Once your goodies are ready, let your children take over again make the food look nice and serve it."
msgstr "✅ Sodra julle lekkernye gereed is, laat jou kinders weer die leiding neem en dit versier en bedien."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "😃 Finally, enjoy the results together!"
msgstr "😃 Uiteindelik kan julle die eindproduk saam geniet!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You will have delicious food AND you’ll also have shared a special bonding moment while developing important skills like patience, focus, and creativity."
msgstr "Jy sal heerlike kos hê EN julle sou ook spesiale tyd saam spandeer het en belangrike vaardighede ontwikkel het soos geduld, fokus en kreatiwiteit."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "So, grab what you need and let the baking fun begin! ✨"
msgstr "So, kry alles wat jy nodig het en laat die bakpret begin!✨"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Secret Handshake*"
msgstr "*Geheime Handdruk*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let’s make a special, fun, and unique handshake that only you and your child share 👋  "
msgstr "Kom ons maak 'n spesiale, prettige en unieke handdruk wat net jy en jou kind deel👋  "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔶 First, sit down together and talk about the kind of handshake you want. Should it be quick and silly, or cool and complicated? It’s totally up to you! "
msgstr "🔶 Eerstens, dink eers oor die tipe handdruk wat julle wil hê. Moet dit vinnig en laf wees, of oulik en ingewikkeld? Dis geheel en al julle keuse! "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎵 You can start by choosing a few simple moves like clapping patterns, high fives, fist bumps, or snapping fingers."
msgstr "🎵 Julle kan begin deur 'n paar eenvoudige bewegings te kies, soos klappatrone, high fives, vuisstampe of vingersklap."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Next, practice adding different steps. Maybe a spin, a shoulder tap, or even a fun dance move. The more creative and playful, the better!"
msgstr "🔄 Volgende, oefen om verskillende stappe by te voeg. Dalk 'n draai, 'n skouertikkie of selfs 'n prettige dansbeweging. Hoe meer kreatief en speels, hoe beter!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💛 Once you’ve mastered your moves, make your secret handshake a part of your routine! Use it as a fun greeting after school, or anytime you want to feel that special connection."
msgstr "💛 Sodra julle die bewegings bemeester het, maak jul geheime handdruk deel van jul roetine! Gebruik dit as 'n prettige manier om te groet na skool, of net wanneer jy daardie spesiale verbintenis wil voel."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This isn’t just about having fun - it helps build your child’s confidence and teamwork skills while creating a special tradition you both can enjoy. ✅"
msgstr "Dit is nie net ter wille van pret nie - dit help om jou kind se selfvertroue en spanwerkvaardighede te bou, terwyl julle 'n spesiale tradisie skep wat albei kan geniet ✅"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Create Silly Characters*"
msgstr "*Skep Lawwe Karakters*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎨 All you need to play this game is a piece of paper and a pen or pencil."
msgstr "🎨 Al wat jy nodig het om die speletjie te speel, is papier en 'n pen of potlood."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "1️⃣ The first person draws the top (head, hat, hair) of a character. This can be as serious or silly as you want it to be."
msgstr "1️⃣ Die eerste persoon teken die bokant (kop, hoed, hare) van 'n karakter. Dit kan so ernstig of so laf wees soos wat jy wil hê dit moet wees."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Fold the drawing to cover up what has been drawn but leave two lines to show where the next person who is drawing should pick up."
msgstr "🔄 Vou die tekening om die getekende gedeelte toe te maak, maar los twee lyne oop om te wys waar die volgende persoon wat moet teken, moet aangaan."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "2️⃣ Pass the paper on to the next person, who, without seeing what has already been drawn, will contribute the next set of features to the character: The shoulders or tummy. Fold the paper back to cover up the image and pass it on."
msgstr "2️⃣ Gee die papier vir die volgende persoon wat, sonder om te weet wat reeds geteken is, die volgende stel kenmerke van die karakter sal byvoeg: Die skouers of magie. Vou die papier terug om die beeld toe te maak en stuur dit aan."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📝 Repeat until someone has drawn the feet of the character and then open your drawing up to see the masterpiece you have created together!"
msgstr "📝 Herhaal totdat iemand die karakter se voete geteken het en maak dan die tekening oop om die meesterstuk wat julle saam geskep het, te sien!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This game builds creativity, nurtures imagination, and helps teach kids to collaborate – while having lots of laughs! 🌈"
msgstr "Hierdie speletjie bou kreatiwiteit, koester verbeelding en help om kinders te leer om saam te werk - terwyl hulle baie pret het! 🌈"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adapted from Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/co-drawing"
msgstr "Aangepas uit Learning Through Play: https://learningthroughplay.com/let-s-play/co-drawing"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Get ready to put your animal knowledge to the test in this exciting guessing game! 🚩"
msgstr "Maak gereed om jou dierekennis te toets in hierdie opwindende raai-raai-speletjie!🚩"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🧸 One person secretly picks an animal - don’t say which animal you’ve chosen! "
msgstr "🧸 Een persoon kies in die geheim 'n dier - moenie sê watter dier jy gekies het nie! "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 The other player asks questions to figure it out. You might ask, “Is the animal a mammal?” or “Can it fly?” Keep going until you guess correctly and then switch. "
msgstr "💡 Die ander speler vra vrae om uit te werk wat die antwoord is. Jy kan vra, \"Is die dier 'n soogdier?\" of \"Kan dit vlieg?\" Hou aan tot jy reg geraai het en ruil dan om. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 You can even play this game with multiple people by taking turns guessing and picking the animal!"
msgstr "🔄 Jy kan selfs die speletjie met meer mense speel deur beurte te maak om te raai en die dier te kies!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂 For added fun, younger kids can join by acting out the animal to give extra clues!"
msgstr "👂 Vir ekstra pret kan jonger kinders die dier naboots om ekstra leidrade te gee!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This game sharpens your child’s reasoning skills and strengthens their memory while having fun ⭐"
msgstr "Hierdie speletjie verskerp jou kind se redeneringsvermoë en hul geheue terwyl hulle pret het ⭐"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*A friendly chat*"
msgstr "*'n Vriendelike geselsie*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Talk to your teen about something that they are interested in! 😃"
msgstr "Praat met jou tiener oor iets waarin hulle belangstel! 😃"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⚽ An easy way to start talking to your teen is to ask them about something they are interested in. For example, you could talk about sports, books, movies, friends, music, celebrities, or school."
msgstr "⚽ 'n Maklike manier om met jou tiener te begin praat, is om hulle uit te vra oor iets waarin hulle belangstel. Julle kan byvoorbeeld praat oor sport, boeke, flieks, vriende, musiek, beroemde mense of skool."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂 You may not find everything your teen shares to be interesting, but it’s important to show enthusiasm and an eagerness to learn."
msgstr "👂 Jy sal dalk nie alles wat jou tiener vertel, interessant vind nie, maar dit is belangrik om te wys dat jy entoesiasties is en gewillig is om te leer."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Create your own Recipe*"
msgstr "*Ontwikkel jou eie Resep*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let your teen come up with a new meal idea! "
msgstr "Laat jou tiener vorendag kom met 'n nuwe idee vir 'n ete! "

#. type=text
#. Strings like @fields.xxx and @results.yyy should not be translated. 
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🍚 Create a new dish with @fields.child_nickname using ingredients they love!"
msgstr "🍚 Skep 'n nuwe gereg saam met @fields.child_nickname deur bestanddele te gebruik waaroor hulle mal is!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔵 Together, choose two ingredients, and ask your teen to prepare a meal using them. For example: chicken and spinach, tomatoes and rice, maize and pumpkin."
msgstr "🔵 Kies saam twee bestanddele, en vra jou tiener om dit te gebruik om 'n ete voor te berei. Byvoorbeeld: hoender en spinasie, tamaties en rys, mielies en pampoen."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📝 If you enjoy the meal, make it something your family eats weekly and ask your teen to write it down for you, give the meal a name, and explain how to make it. "
msgstr "📝 As julle die ete geniet, maak dit iets wat jou gesin weekliks eet, en vra jou tiener om dit vir jou neer te skryf, gee die gereg 'n naam en verduidelik hoe om dit te maak. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "✨ If your teen notices that you are learning from their cooking, it will boost their confidence!"
msgstr "✨ As jou tiener sien dat jy uit hulle kookvernuf leer, sal dit hulle selfvertroue 'n hupstoot gee!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🍚 Create a new dish with your teen using ingredients they love!"
msgstr "🍚 Skep 'n nuwe gereg saam met jou tiener deur bestanddele te gebruik waaroor hulle mal is!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Reflect on the positive*"
msgstr "*Dink na oor die positiewe*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Spread Positivity! 🌈"
msgstr "Versprei Positiwiteit! 🌈"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 Together, take a minute to think about all the things you did today. "
msgstr "💡 Neem saam 'n minuut om na te dink oor al die goed wat julle vandag gedoen het. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "☀️ Take turns sharing one positive or fun thing that happened. This could be something small, like feeling good because you cleaned the house, or something big, like spending time with family and friends. "
msgstr "☀️ Neem beurte om een positiewe of prettige ding wat gebeur het, te deel. Dit kan iets kleins wees, soos om goed te voel omdat julle die huis skoongemaak het, of iets groots, soos dat julle tyd saam met familie en vriende deurgebring het. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⏰ Try doing this every day - even more on the days it feels like you have not done anything special."
msgstr "⏰ Probeer om dit elke dag te doen - veral op die dae wat dit voel asof julle nie enigiets spesiaals gedoen het nie."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*What’s new?*"
msgstr "*Wat’s nuut?*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Learning is fun! 🎓"
msgstr "Leer is pret! 🎓"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "❓ Ask your teen to think of a new, fun skill you could learn together. "
msgstr "❓ Vra jou tiener om te dink aan 'n nuwe, pret-vaardigheid wat julle saam kan leer. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Take turns trying out the new skill.  Make sure to praise each other and learn and play together!"
msgstr "🔄 Neem beurte om die nuwe vaardigheid te probeer. Maak seker dat julle mekaar prys, leer en saam speel!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💛 Approach learning the skill in a kind and fun way, and do not judge your teen or yourself for your ability in the skill."
msgstr "💛 Benader die leer van die vaardigheid op 'n simpatieke en prettige manier, en moenie jouself of jou tiener afkraak oor julle vermoë in die vaardigheid nie."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Dance moves*"
msgstr "*Danspassies*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let's get moving! 👋 Dancing is a great way to exercise, have fun, and bond with your teen at the same time! You both get to express yourselves in a fun, relaxed way.  🎵 "
msgstr "Kom ons beweeg! 👋 Dans is 'n wonderlike manier om te oefen, pret te hê, en terselfdertyd 'n band met jou tiener te vorm! Julle kry albei kans om julself op 'n prettige, ontspanne manier uit te druk.  🎵 "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This game can be played in pairs or a group with everyone taking turns being the leader:"
msgstr "Hierdie speletjie kan in pare of in 'n groep gespeel word, met almal wat beurte neem om die leier te wees:"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📱 Let your teen choose a song they like and create a set of dance moves."
msgstr "📱 Laat jou tiener 'n liedjie kies waarvan hulle hou en ontwikkel 'n stel danspassies."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 First person does a dance move and everyone else copies it."
msgstr "👀 Die eerste persoon voer 'n danspassie uit en al die ander moet dit namaak."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "☀️ Don’t worry about perfecting the dance moves, it’s all about having fun together!"
msgstr "☀️ Moenie bekommerd wees as jul danspassies nie perfek is nie, dit gaan daaroor om saam pret te hê!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 If you want to, you can perform your dance for the household!"
msgstr "💡 As jy wil, kan jy jou dans vir die huismense doen!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Dance Activity*"
msgstr "*Dansaktiwiteit*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Try something new and learn a dance challenge with your teen! ✨ Have fun!"
msgstr "Probeer iets nuuts en leer 'n dansuitdaging saam met jou tiener! ✨ Geniet dit!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⭐ Dancing is a great way to have fun together while being creative and moving your body!"
msgstr "⭐ Dans is 'n wonderlike manier om saam pret te hê terwyl julle kreatief besig is en jul liggame beweeg!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📱 If your teen uses the app TikTok, suggest doing a dance challenge together."
msgstr "📱 As jou tiener die app TikTok gebruik, stel voor dat julle saam 'n dansuitdaging doen."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "😃 Ask your teen to choose their favourite dance and learn it with them."
msgstr "😃 Vra jou tiener om hulle gunsteling dans te kies, en leer dit saam met hulle."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎉 It’s okay if you can’t dance well, have fun and try not to take it too seriously! "
msgstr "🎉 Dis oukei as jy nie goed kan dans nie, geniet dit en probeer om dit nie te ernstig op te neem nie! "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 You do not have to post the video to learn the dance. You can keep it as a memory between you and your teen."
msgstr "💡 Julle hoef nie die video op sosiale media te plaas om die dans te leer nie. Jy en jou tiener kan dit net vir julself as 'n herinnering hou."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Check-in chat*"
msgstr "*Inklok Klets*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Actively checking in on one another helps to keep relationships healthy! ⭐"
msgstr "Om aktief te kyk of die ander een oukei is, help om verhoudings gesond te hou! ⭐"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Ask each other questions: “What made you happy today?” 👂 “What was difficult today?” 👂 “How can I help you?” 👂"
msgstr "Vra vir mekaar vrae: “Wat het jou vandag gelukkig gemaak?” 👂 “Wat was vandag moeilik?” 👂 “Hoe kan ek jou help?” 👂"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "For this to help, your teen needs to feel safe while sharing things with you. Be open to their responses. 💚 Teens tend to be more honest when they trust that what they say will not be used against them later."
msgstr "Dit sal slegs help as jou tiener veilig voel wanneer hulle goed met jou deel. Wees oop vir hulle antwoorde. 💚 Tieners is geneig om eerliker te wees as hulle vertrou dat wat hulle sê, nie later teen hulle gebruik sal word nie."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Go easy on yourself if your teen does not want to share their problems with you. 💙 Often, teens are afraid to share as they are scared they will get in trouble. Getting upset with them won’t help - keep showing you love them and give them time! 🌷"
msgstr "Wees gaaf met jouself as jou tiener nie hulle probleme met jou wil deel nie. 💙 Tieners is dikwels bang om te deel, want hulle is bang hulle sal in die moeilikheid kom. Om vir hulle kwaad te word, sal nie help nie - hou aan om te wys dat jy lief is vir hulle en gee hulle tyd! 🌷"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Express Yourself*"
msgstr "*Gee uiting aan Jouself*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Dancing makes people happy!"
msgstr "Dans maak mense gelukkig!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🌈 This game can be played in pairs or as a group - stand facing each other or in a circle."
msgstr "🌈 Hierdie speletjie kan in pare of as 'n groep gespeel word - staan teenoor mekaar of in 'n sirkel."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎵 Together, choose a fun and upbeat song to play and a person to start the game by creating one dance move."
msgstr "🎵 Kies saam 'n prettige, opgewekte liedjie om te speel en 'n persoon om die speletjie te begin deur een danspassie te skep."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 The person to their right must copy that dance move and add their own move to it."
msgstr "👀 Die persoon aan hulle regterkant moet daardie danspassie naboots en hulle eie danspassie byvoeg."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "✨ Go around the circle, each person adding their own dance move to the full song."
msgstr "✨ Gaan in die rondte, elke persoon voeg hulle eie danspassie by tot aan die einde van die liedjie."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 The first one who forgets someone's dance moves or does it in the wrong order chooses the next song and starts the game again."
msgstr "🔄 Die eerste een wat iemand se danspassies vergeet of dit in die verkeerde volgorde doen, kies die volgende liedjie en begin weer die speletjie."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎉 Try new dance moves with this game and have fun!"
msgstr "🎉 Probeer nuwe danspassies met hierdie speletjie en geniet dit!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*2 Truths, 1 Lie*"
msgstr "*2 Waarhede, 1 Leuen*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This is a fun, quick game, and the point of it is to learn things about each other. Make your answers as interesting as possible! 🎨"
msgstr "Hierdie speletjie is prettig en vinnig, en die doel daarvan is om meer oor mekaar uit te vind. Maak jou antwoorde so interessant as moontlik! 🎨"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 Think of 3 facts about yourself. 2 must be true, 1 must be a lie. "
msgstr "💡 Dink aan 3 stellings oor jouself. 2 moet waar wees en 1 moet 'n leuen wees. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔷 Here are some examples: I hate bananas, I have travelled to Kenya, my favourite subject in school was maths."
msgstr "🔷 Hier is 'n paar voorbeelde: Ek haat piesangs, ek het na Kenia gereis, my gunsteling skoolvak was Wiskunde."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 Share the facts with your teen and ask them to guess which one is a lie. "
msgstr "👀 Deel die feite met jou tiener en vra hulle om te raai watter een 'n leuen is. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Now ask them to do the same, and guess theirs."
msgstr "🔄 Vra hulle nou om dieselfde te doen, en raai hulle s'n."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Did you learn anything new about your teen, or did they learn anything new about you? 💛"
msgstr "Het jy enigiets nuuts oor jou tiener uitgevind, of het hulle iets nuuts oor jou uitgevind? 💛"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Yes, No or Maybe*"
msgstr "*Ja, Nee of Miskien*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Are you tired of hearing your teen say yes, no, or maybe to all of your questions? Turn your chat into a game, and don’t allow one-word answers. 🎈"
msgstr "Is jy moeg daarvan dat jou tiener ja, nee of miskien op al jou vrae antwoord? Verander julle geselsie in 'n speletjie, en moenie eenwoord-antwoorde toelaat nie. 🎈"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔴 Teens are known to give one-word answers to avoid talking. "
msgstr "🔴 Tieners is bekend daarvoor dat hulle eenwoord-antwoorde gee om 'n gesprek te vermy. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 When you would like to really know how your teen is doing, you can turn your chat into a game. "
msgstr "💡 As jy regtig wil weet hoe dit met jou tiener gaan, kan jy julle geselsie in 'n speletjie verander. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⭐ Take turns asking each other questions. The only rule is that you cannot use one-word responses, such as Yes, No, Maybe, Fine, and Okay."
msgstr "⭐ Neem beurte om mekaar vrae te vra. Die enigste reël is dat julle nie eenwoord-antwoorde mag gee nie, soos Ja, Nee, Miskien, Goed en Oukei."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⚽ You can ask about things your teen likes or what they did today. For example, how was your day? What are you excited for? Is there anything worrying you?"
msgstr "⚽ Jy kan uitvra oor goed waarvan jou tiener hou of wat hulle vandag gedoen het. Byvoorbeeld, Hoe was jou dag? Waaroor is jy opgewonde? Is daar iets waaroor jy jou bekommer?"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 It is important to let your teen ask a question as well. Trust is built when your teen can see that you are also sharing your life with them, and not only trying to learn about their life."
msgstr "🔄 Dit is belangrik om jou tiener toe te laat om ook 'n vraag te vra. Vertroue word gebou wanneer jou tiener kan sien dat jy ook jou lewe met hulle deel, en nie slegs probeer om meer oor hulle lewe uit te vind nie."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Movie World*"
msgstr "*Fliek-Wêreld*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Leaving the busy and stressful world behind can be good for our health. 🌱 Take a moment to escape with your teen by creating a superhero story together!"
msgstr "Om die besige en stresvolle wêreld agter te laat, kan goed wees vir ons gesondheid. 🌱 Neem 'n oomblik om saam met jou tiener te ontsnap deur saam 'n superheld-storie te skep!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎈 Ask your teen to imagine that they are a superhero and what their superpowers would be. Flying? Time travel? Mind reading? Super Strength?"
msgstr "🎈Vra jou tiener om hulle te verbeel dat hulle 'n superheld is, en wat hulle superkragte sou wees. Vlieg? Tydreis? Gedagtes lees? Super Sterkte?"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "✨ Ask them how they would use these superpowers, and why. "
msgstr "✨ Vra hoe hulle hierdie superkragte sou gebruik, en hoekom. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🌈 Help them give their superhero a name, an outfit, and a sidekick, and act it out. If your teen does not want to act, that is fine - talking about it is just as good!"
msgstr "🌈 Help hulle om hulle superheld 'n naam te gee, asook 'n uitrusting en 'n helper, en speel hierdie rolle. As jou tiener nie wil toneelspeel nie, is dit oukei - dis net so goed om daaroor te praat!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👑 Now, let them make up a superhero for you. Play the part! You can ask questions, like who the villain would be, or how you became a superhero. "
msgstr "👑 Laat hulle nou vir jou 'n superheld uitdink. Speel die rol! Jy kan vrae vra, soos wie die skurk sou wees, of hoe jy 'n superheld geword het. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 Create a story - what happens to the characters? Is it an action story? Is it a thriller, space, sport, adventure, or romance?"
msgstr "💡 Skep 'n storie - wat gebeur met die karakters? Is dit 'n aksiestorie? Is dit 'n riller, ruimte, sport, avontuur of romanse?"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "➡️ Next time you play this game, you could create a new story or superhero with your teen or continue the story you started together."
msgstr "➡️ Volgende keer wat julle hierdie speletjie speel, kan jy saam met jou tiener 'n nuwe storie skep of voortgaan met die storie wat julle saam begin het."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Exercise is a great way to spend time together and it is so good for your health. 🌱 Find a sport or exercise that both you and your teen want to do and try it out together! "
msgstr "Oefening is 'n wonderlike manier om tyd saam deur te bring, en dit is so goed vir jou gesondheid. 🌱 Vind 'n sport of oefening wat jy en jou tiener albei wil doen en probeer dit saam! "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⚽ Together you can walk, run, play soccer, swim, dance, or do any other sport.."
msgstr "⚽ Saam kan julle stap, hardloop, sokker speel, swem, dans, of enige ander sport doen."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 If you or your teen do not like the first exercise you pick, try a new exercise."
msgstr "🔄 As jy of jou tiener nie hou van die eerste oefening wat julle gekies het nie, probeer 'n nuwe een."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Make up a story*"
msgstr "*Dink 'n storie uit*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Creating stories together is a great way to learn the art of storytelling - and to build your teen’s creativity! 📖"
msgstr "Om saam stories te skep, is 'n wonderlike manier om die kuns van storievertel aan te leer - en jou tiener se kreatiwiteit te ontwikkel! 📖"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔟 With your teen, come up with 10 words to use. They can be any words you want! For example: banana, spaceship, fish, water, painting, wasp nest, cooking, wedding."
msgstr "🔟 Dink saam met jou tiener aan 10 woorde om te gebruik. Dit kan enige woorde wees wat julle wil! Byvoorbeeld: piesang, ruimtetuig, vis, water, skildery, perdebynes, kook, troue."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎂 Start your story with, “Once upon a time, there was a…” and make sure you use one of the words from the list in your sentence. For example, “Once upon a time, there was a family who worked on a *banana* farm.”"
msgstr "🎂 Begin julle storie met “Eendag, lank, lank gelede was daar 'n…” en maak seker dat julle een van die woorde uit die lys in julle sin gebruik. Byvoorbeeld, “Eendag, lank, lank gelede was daar 'n gesin wat op 'n *piesang*-plaas gewerk het.”"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📝 Let your teen make up the next sentence using another word from the list."
msgstr "📝 Laat jou tiener die volgende sin uitdink deur nog 'n woord uit die lys te gebruik."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Take turns until you have used as many words from the list as you can, or until you have finished your story. "
msgstr "🔄 Neem beurte totdat julle soveel as moontlik woorde uit die lys gebruik het, of totdat julle die storie voltooi het. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔔 Be as creative as possible with your story and do not tell your teen what to say. It does not need to be a real story to be a good story!"
msgstr "🔔 Wees so kreatief as moontlik met julle storie, en moenie vir jou tiener voorskryf wat om te sê nie. Dit hoef nie 'n ware storie te wees om 'n goeie storie te wees nie!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎁 Ask your teen what their favourite part of the story was, and tell them yours!"
msgstr "🎁 Vra jou tiener wat hulle gunsteling deel van die storie was, en sê wat joune was!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Take A Pause with your teen*"
msgstr "*Ontspan 'n rukkie saam met jou tiener*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Take a pause with your teen. This helps them deal with stress in a healthy way!"
msgstr "Ontspan 'n rukkie saam met jou tiener. Dit help hulle om stres op 'n gesonde manier te hanteer!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⏰ You could take a pause before dinner, after school, before school, or before bedtime."
msgstr "⏰ Julle kan voor aandete, na skool, voor skool of voor slaaptyd 'n bietjie ontspan."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👂 Sit down together and close your eyes. Listen to your breath as it goes in and out. Notice how you feel. "
msgstr "👂 Gaan sit saam en maak julle oë toe. Luister na jul asemhaling terwyl julle in- en uitasem. Neem kennis van hoe julle voel. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⭐ Take 5 more deep breaths."
msgstr "⭐ Haal nog 5 keer diep asem."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 When you are ready, open your eyes again. Do you feel any different? "
msgstr "👀 Wanneer julle gereed is, maak jul oë weer oop. Voel julle enigsins anders? "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⏸ Ask your teen what it was like to take a pause. Listen and accept whatever they say about it."
msgstr "⏸ Vra jou tiener hoe dit was om 'n rukkie te ontspan. Luister en aanvaar wat ook al hulle daaroor sê."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Name That Tune*"
msgstr "*Liedjieraai*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Listening to music is a great way to lower your stress and have fun with your family. 💚"
msgstr "Om na musiek te luister, is 'n wonderlike manier om jou stresvlakke te laat daal en pret saam met jou gesin te hê. 💚"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📻 Gather your family members and choose one person to play, sing or hum a song."
msgstr "📻 Kry jou familielede bymekaar en kies een persoon om 'n liedjie te speel, sing of neurie."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "❓ Everyone else must guess the name and artist of the song."
msgstr "❓ Al die ander moet die naam en kunstenaar van die liedjie raai."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎉 The first one to guess it right becomes the next person to sing or play a song. "
msgstr "🎉 Die eerste een wat reg raai, is die volgende persoon wat 'n liedjie speel of sing. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Keep going around until everyone has been able to play their favourite song and let the rest hear."
msgstr "🔄 Hou so aan totdat almal 'n beurt gehad het om hul gunsteling liedjie te speel/sing en die res laat luister het."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Pass the ball*"
msgstr "*Gee die bal aan*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "➡️ Start in a circle and pass the ball around. "
msgstr "➡️ Begin in 'n sirkel en gee die bal aan. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Make Housework Fun*"
msgstr "*Maak Huistake Pret*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Turn your chores into games! 🏆 "
msgstr "Verander jul huistake in speletjies! 🏆 "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "☀️ Making housework fun is a good way to teach your teen to be responsible and to rely on themselves. "
msgstr "☀️ Om huiswerk pret te maak, is 'n goeie manier om jou tiener verantwoordelikheid te leer en om op hulself staat te maak. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📝 Together, make a list of all the chores that must be done in your home. "
msgstr "📝 Maak saam 'n lysie van al die huistake wat in julle huis gedoen moet word. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 Make sure the tasks are fair and things your teen can do. For example, washing up, sweeping, mopping, making the beds, and laundry."
msgstr "💡 Maak seker die take is regverdig en dat dit goed is wat jou tiener kan doen. Byvoorbeeld, skottelgoed, vee, mop, beddens opmaak en wasgoed."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Each week, let a different person in the family choose a chore first."
msgstr "🔄 Laat 'n ander persoon in die gesin elke week eerste 'n taak kies."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎵 Play some music or turn on the radio. Music is a great way to make a boring task fun!"
msgstr "🎵 Speel musiek of skakel die radio aan. Musiek is 'n wonderlike manier om 'n vervelige taak prettig te maak!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "✅ Tick off the tasks when they are done so you can see your progress as a family. You could offer small rewards as motivation to complete activities."
msgstr "✅ Merk die take af wanneer dit klaar is, sodat julle as gesin jul vordering kan sien. Jy kan klein belonings as motivering aanbied om aktiwiteite te voltooi."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📺 For example, you could let your teen watch more TV, spend more time with their friends, choose what they want for dinner, or have something sweet if they do their chores in a fair amount of time."
msgstr "📺 Jy kan byvoorbeeld jou tiener meer TV laat kyk, meer tyd saam met vriende laat deurbring, laat kies wat hulle vir aandete wil hê, of soetgoed gee as hulle, hulle take binne 'n redelike tyd afhandel."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "❓ If your child does not complete a chore, ask them why, and come up with a fair consequence together."
msgstr "❓ As jou kind nie 'n taak afhandel nie, vra hulle hoekom, en dink saam 'n regverdige gevolg uit."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*I’m Going on a Picnic and I Will Bring…*"
msgstr "*Ek Gaan na 'n Piekniek en Ek Bring Saam …*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Memory games are a fun way to strengthen our brains! "
msgstr "Geheuespeletjies is 'n prettige manier om ons breine te versterk! "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎂 Think of all the things you would have at your dream picnic. "
msgstr "🎂 Dink aan al die goed wat jy by jou droompiekniek sal hê. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎈 The first person says, “On Saturday, I am going to the park to have a picnic. To this picnic, I will bring...” and they say one thing they will bring to the picnic."
msgstr "🎈 Die eerste persoon sê, “Saterdag gaan ek in die park piekniek hou. Vir die piekniek bring ek...” en noem een ding wat hulle saamneem vir die piekniek."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🍅 For example: a sandwich, a ball, a blanket, forks, cups, a dog, or coca cola."
msgstr "🍅 Byvoorbeeld: 'n toebroodjie, 'n bal, 'n kombers, vurke, koppies, 'n hond of coca cola."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔔 The second person adds to the first person's list, but must start at the beginning: “On Saturday, I am going to the park to have a picnic. To this picnic, I will bring...” and say the item that the first person said AND then add their own item to the list."
msgstr "🔔 Die tweede persoon voeg by die eerste persoon se lys aan, maar moet weer oor begin: “Saterdag gaan ek in die park piekniek hou. Vir die piekniek bring ek...” en sê die item wat die eerste persoon gesê het EN voeg dan hulle eie item by die lys."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Each time you add an item, you must say all previous items first - in the correct order!"
msgstr "🔄 Elke keer as jy 'n item byvoeg, moet jy eers al die vorige items sê - in die korrekte volgorde!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⭐ Each person adds to the list, while remembering all the previous items. "
msgstr "⭐ Elke persoon voeg 'n item by die lys, terwyl hulle al die vorige items onthou. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👀 If everyone has a turn, keep going and building your list. The first person to forget an item restarts the game!"
msgstr "👀 As almal 'n beurt gehad het, hou aan om die lys langer te maak. Die eerste persoon wat 'n item vergeet, begin die speletjie oor!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*This is who I am*"
msgstr "* Dit is wie ek is*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Self-esteem is the way you value yourself, either in a positive or negative way. Helping your teen to have high self-esteem is a recipe for success! 🏆"
msgstr "Selfbeeld is die manier waarop jy jouself na waarde skat, op 'n positiewe of negatiewe manier. Om jou tiener te help om 'n goeie selfbeeld te hê, is 'n suksesresep! 🏆"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⭐Share with your teen 3 things you like about yourself!"
msgstr "⭐Deel met jou tiener 3 dinge van jouself waarvan jy hou!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "3️⃣ Ask your teen to tell you 3 things they like about themselves. "
msgstr "3️⃣ Vra jou tiener om vir jou 3 dinge van hulself te noem waaarvan hulle hou. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "For example: I am great at treating others kindly. I am great at styling my hair. I am great at football. ⚽"
msgstr "Byvoorbeeld: Ek is wonderlik daarmee om ander mense goed te behandel. Ek kan my hare baie goed versorg. Ek is fantasties in sokker. ⚽"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "If your teen does not feel comfortable sharing these, ask them to write them down. 📝"
msgstr "As jou tiener nie gemaklik daarmee voel om hierdie dinge te sê nie, vra hulle om dit neer te skryf. 📝"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Things I like about others and me*"
msgstr "*Dinge in ander en myself waarvan ek hou*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "☀️Ask your teen to share 3 things they like about a friend or someone they admire, like a celebrity."
msgstr "☀️Vra jou tiener om 3 dinge te noem waarvan hulle hou in 'n vriend of iemand wat hulle bewonder, soos 'n beroemde persoon."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "❓ Ask them if they share any of these qualities, too."
msgstr "❓ Vra hulle of hulle ook oor enige van hierdie eienskappe beskik."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💙 You can do the same: share with your teen the qualities you like about yourself or about someone you admire - and what you like about your teen!"
msgstr "💙 Jy kan dieselfde doen: deel met jou tiener die eienskappe waarvan jy in jouself of iemand wat jy bewonder, hou - en waarvan jy in jou tiener hou!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Make a family wish list*"
msgstr "*Stel 'n gesins wenslys op*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Wish lists are a great way to set, plan and keep track of your goals and dreams. 🌷 "
msgstr "Wenslyste is 'n wonderlike manier om julle doelwitte en drome vas te stel, te beplan en die vordering daarvan dop te hou. 🌷 "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📝 To start your wish list, gather your family together and grab pens and paper. "
msgstr "📝 Om met julle wenslys te begin, kry jou gesin bymekaar en gryp penne en papier. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🚲 Allow each family member to write a list of goals and experiences they want to achieve this year."
msgstr "🚲 Laat elke gesinslid 'n lys van doelwitte en ervarings wat hulle vanjaar wil behaal en ervaar, neerskryf."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎂 For example: exercise daily, read 1 book a month, make a new friend, learn to bake a cake, learn to juggle, or go watch the local soccer team play. "
msgstr "🎂 Byvoorbeeld: oefen daagliks, lees 1 boek per maand, maak 'n nuwe vriend, leer om koek te bak, leer om te \"juggle\", of gaan kyk wanneer die plaaslike sokkerspan speel. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔔 Once you have finished, put the list up where everyone can see it daily."
msgstr "🔔 Wanneer julle klaar is, sit die lys iewers op waar almal dit elke dag kan sien."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎉 As members of the family reach their goals, tick them off the list and celebrate each goal reached. "
msgstr "🎉 Wanneer gesinslede hul doelwitte bereik, merk dit af op die lys en vier elke doelwit wat behaal is. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "❓ As the year goes on, there might be some items some of you have not achieved. Talk to your family about whether you still want to reach this goal or whether the goal has changed. "
msgstr "❓ Soos die jaar verbygaan, is daar dalk van die items wat sommige van julle nog nie behaal het nie. Praat met jou gesin oor of julle steeds hierdie doelwit wil bereik en of die doelwit dalk verander het. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔑 If you still want to achieve the goal, discuss with your family what you need to do to tick the goal off your wish list."
msgstr "🔑 As jy steeds die doelwit wil behaal, bespreek met jou gesin wat jy moet doen om dit op jou wenslysie te kan afmerk."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Weekly Goal Setting*"
msgstr "*Weeklikse Doelwitstelling*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let’s set some goals ⭐"
msgstr "Kom ons stel 'n paar doelwitte vas ⭐"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⏰ It can be helpful to set smaller weekly goals that are easier to reach. This helps us reach our larger goals over time."
msgstr "⏰ Dit kan help om kleiner weeklikse doelwitte te stel wat makliker is om te bereik. Dit help ons om ons groter doelwitte mettertyd te bereik."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡Ask your teen for one goal that they would like to achieve this week. "
msgstr "💡Vra jou tiener vir een doelwit wat hulle graag hierdie week wil bereik. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔄 Make sure this goal is *specific* and  *achievable* to reach in 1 week."
msgstr "🔄 Maak seker hierdie doelwit is *spesifiek* en *bereikbaar* om in 1 week te bereik."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💚 You can also share your own weekly goal with your teen and support each other so you can both achieve your goals."
msgstr "💚 Jy kan ook jou eie weeklikse doel met jou tiener deel en julle kan mekaar ondersteun sodat julle albei jul doelwitte kan bereik."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🎉 Make sure to praise and celebrate your teen for their hard work towards reaching their goal."
msgstr "🎉 Maak seker dat jy jou tiener prys en vier vir hulle harde werk om hulle doelwit te bereik."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔔 If your teen does not reach their goal, that is okay. Discuss with your teen the steps they still need to take or how they could reach it a different way."
msgstr "🔔 As jou tiener nie hulle doelwit bereik nie, is dit oukei. Bespreek die stappe met jou tiener wat hulle nog moet volg of hoe hulle dit op 'n ander manier kan bereik."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Think Big, Think Small*"
msgstr "*Dink Groot, Dink Klein\""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Working towards big goals can be hard! Here is a way you can help your teen set new goals for the things they want to achieve. 👑"
msgstr "Om na groot doelwitte te werk, kan moeilik wees! Hier is 'n manier waarop jy jou tiener kan help om nuwe doelwitte te stel vir dit wat hulle wil bereik. 👑"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👑 Ask your teen to come up with three things that they are good at, and discuss what they did to become so good at them. For example: keeping their room neat, helping your family with housework, or playing a sport."
msgstr "👑 Vra jou tiener om drie dinge waarmee hulle goed is, te noem, en bespreek wat hulle gedoen het om so goed daarin te word. Byvoorbeeld: om hulle kamer skoon te hou, om die gesin met huistake te help, of 'n sport te speel."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🏆 Next, ask your teen what they wish they were good at. "
msgstr "🏆 Vra jou tiener volgende wat hulle wens hulle mee goed was. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔑 Remind them that it took work and practice to become good at the skills they have. They will have to do the same for any new goal."
msgstr "🔑 Herinner hulle dat dit werk en oefening gekos het om goed te raak in die vaardighede wat hulle het. Hulle sal dieselfde moet doen vir enige nuwe doelwit."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⏰ Help your teen break down their goal and set up smaller goals they need to achieve to reach their greater goal."
msgstr "⏰ Help jou tiener om hulle doelwit op te breek in kleiner doelwitte wat bereik moet word om hulle groot doelwit te bereik."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "📝 It is much easier to achieve a goal if you write it down! This way, you can be reminded of it as you work towards it."
msgstr "📝 Dit is baie makliker om 'n doelwit te bereik as jy dit neerskryf! So kan jy daaraan herinner word terwyl jy daaraan werk."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "☀️ For example, if the goal is to be good at football, small weekly goals could be to go to football practice 2 times per week, run at least 1 km 5 times per week, and learn about the sport from other football players in the community or from books or videos they find. "
msgstr "☀️ As die doelwit byvoorbeeld is om goed in sokker te wees, kan klein weeklikse doelwitte wees om 2 keer per week sokkeroefening by te woon, ten minste 1 km 5 maal per week te hardloop, en om van ander sokkerspelers in die gemeenskap oor die sport te leer of uit boeke of video's wat hulle kry. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "✅ It is important to write down these smaller goals and let your teen tick off each task as they do them each week. Seeing themselves reach smaller goals will keep them motivated to achieve the big goal!"
msgstr "✅ Dit is belangrik vir jou tiener om hierdie kleiner doelwitte neer te skryf en elke taak af te merk soos hulle dit elke week doen. Om te sien hoe hulle kleiner doelwitte bereik, sal hulle gemotiveerd hou om die groot doelwit te bereik!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Role Playing*"
msgstr "*Rolspel*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let’s start acting! ⭐"
msgstr "Kom ons speel toneel! ⭐"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "❓ Role playing common stressful social moments with your teen allows them to practise how to respond so they are prepared if this moment does happen. 🌷"
msgstr "❓ Om algemene stresvolle sosiale oomblikke met jou tiener te rolspel, laat hom/haar toe om voorbereid te wees en te weet hoe om te reageer wanneer dit werklik gebeur. 🌷"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "✨ Ask your teen if they want to role play with you. You can also suggest a topic. For example, asking someone on a date, saying no to drugs/alcohol/sexting, dealing with a bully, getting a bad grade, or dealing with gossip."
msgstr "✨ Vra jou tiener of hulle saam met jou rolspel wil doen. Jy kan ook 'n onderwerp voorstel. Byvoorbeeld, om iemand uit te vra vir 'n afspraak, nee te sê vir dwelms/alkohol/seksboodskappe (\"sexting\"), om 'n boelie te hanteer, swak punte te kry of skinderpraatjies te hanteer."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🌙 Your teen could play the role of a friend asking you to drink at a party. You could role play an underage teen who does not want to drink. Encourage your teen to be silly and really get into character with them. "
msgstr "🌙 Jou tiener kan die rol speel van 'n vriend wat jou by 'n partytjie vra om te drink. Jy kan die rol van 'n minderjarige tiener speel wat nie wil drink nie. Moedig jou tiener aan om laf te wees en regtig saam met jou in karakter te kom. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⏯️ After you act out the scene, it is important to talk to your teen about the actions that you role played. You can act out this scenario as many times as you like!"
msgstr "⏯️ Nadat julle die toneel uitgespeel het, is dit belangrik om met jou tiener te praat oor die aksies wat julle gerolspeel het. Julle kan hierdie scenario soveel keer speel as wat julle wil!"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Traffic Lights*"
msgstr "*Robotte*"

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "A group activity is a great way to bond with others! 💛 "
msgstr "'n Groepsaktiwiteit is 'n wonderlike manier om bande met ander te bou! 💛 "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💡 Choose one person to turn and face a wall. This will be the traffic officer. "
msgstr "💡 Kies een persoon om om te draai en na die muur te kyk. Dit is dan die verkeersbeampte. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🏁 Everyone else will begin the game at the other side of the room, or if you are outside, at a starting line. Set a long distance between the traffic officer and the players."
msgstr "🏁 Al die ander spelers begin die speletjie aan die anderkant van die vertrek, of as julle buite is, op 'n wegspringstreep. Daar moet 'n lang afstand tussen die verkeersbeampte en die spelers wees."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "💚 The game begins when the officer shouts “Green”, and everyone can start moving towards the traffic officer at any speed they choose. "
msgstr "💚 Die speletjie begin wanneer die beampte “Groen” skree, en almal begin na die verkeersbeampte beweeg teen die spoed van hulle keuse. "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🔴 The officer can shout “Red!” at any time, without looking behind them. When they shout this, everyone must stop and freeze! "
msgstr "🔴 Die beampte kan enige tyd “Rooi!” skree, sonder om agter hulle te kyk. Wanneer hulle dit skree, moet almal stop en vries! "

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "⏸ The officer turns around to see if everyone is frozen. If they see anyone moving, they have to send them back to the start line."
msgstr "⏸ Die beampte draai om, om te sien of almal gevries het. As hulle iemand sien beweeg, moet hulle die persoon na die wegspringstreep terugstuur."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "🏆 The winner is the first person to get to the officer without being sent back to the start."
msgstr "🏆 Die wenner is die eerste persoon wat tot by die beampte kom sonder om na die wegspringstreep teruggestuur te word."

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "👑 The winner then becomes the traffic officer and you can play another round!"
msgstr "👑 Die wenner word dan die verkeersbeampte en julle kan nog 'n rondte speel!"

